{"id": "6811", "revid": "189481", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6811", "title": "Todesfaelle Flamme", "text": "Todesfaelle Flamme is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Zweihander\"&gt;Zweihander&lt;/a&gt; from \"\".\nTodesfaelle Flamme can be equated to a weaker version of &lt;a href=\"Flamebellow\"&gt;Flamebellow&lt;/a&gt;, due to its similar effects.\nLike its name implies, Todesfaelle Flamme adds a very large amount of &lt;a href=\"Fire\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage to its attacks. Although many enemies are immune to fire in &lt;a href=\"difficulty\"&gt;difficulty&lt;/a&gt;, this does not necessarily downgrade Todesfaelle Flamme's effectiveness, as it is still a powerful weapon nonetheless.\nIn terms of other properties, Todesfaelle Flamme also gives its user the ability to cast the spells and &lt;a href=\"Enchant\"&gt;Enchant&lt;/a&gt;. Although Fire Wall is useful for its stacking damage, a physical fighter would most likely find Enchant more effective for their purposes.\nTodesfaelle Flamme, on the defensive side, gives a good boost to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Resist\"&gt;Fire Resist&lt;/a&gt; that can be very useful in later game modes. When combined with other fire resistant equipment (or even another fire resistant weapon such as &lt;a href=\"Hexfire\"&gt;Hexfire&lt;/a&gt;, in the case of a ), it can increase fire resist to levels as high as 95, even in Hell difficulty.\nStats.\nOne-Hand Damage: (41-49) To (77-91)\nTwo-Hand Damage: (63-75) To (118-140)\nDurability: 50\nRequired Level: 46\nRequired Strength: 125\nRequired Dexterity: 94\nSword Class - "}
