{"id": "6983", "revid": "50300896", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6983", "title": "Tomb Reaver", "text": "Tomb Reaver is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Cryptic%20Axe\"&gt;Cryptic Axe&lt;/a&gt; from \"\".\nWith a high damage output, the useful ability to resurrect fallen enemies, and a boost to &lt;a href=\"Resistances\"&gt;Resistances&lt;/a&gt;, Tomb Reaver is a safe, all-around good weapon for physical fighters. Its boost to &lt;a href=\"Magic%20find\"&gt;Magic find&lt;/a&gt; is particularly useful for treasure hunters.\n&lt;a href=\"Ethereal%20Items\"&gt;Ethereal&lt;/a&gt; Tomb Reavers with 3 sockets and good stats are among the rarest and most sought-after items in the game, since they can be socketed with and other &lt;a href=\"runes\"&gt;runes&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"jewels\"&gt;jewels&lt;/a&gt; to boost their raw damage and become one of the most powerful weapons for melee fighters specializing in magic find.\nStats.\nTwo-Hand Damage: (99-125) To (450-570)\nRequired Level: 84\nRequired Strength: 165\nRequired Dexterity: 103\nDurability: 65\nPolearm Class - \nTrivia.\nThe name appears to be a reference to two Eidos games: Tomb Raider and Soul Reaver.\nIn Tomb Raider, the main character is an adventurer treasure hunter, explaining the Light Radius, Better Chance of Getting Magic Items and Enhanced Damage effects, while in Soul Reaver the main character is a reanimated vampire ghostly entity that feeds on souls and shifts between the regular and astral plane, explaining the Increased Damage and Attack Raiting to Undead, increased Resistances, chance to Reanimate and Life Leech effects."}
{"id": "36041", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36041", "title": "Tomb Roach", "text": "Roaches are &lt;a href=\"animal\"&gt;insects&lt;/a&gt; found throughout &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;, especially around tombs and other burial sites . \nLore.\nThese voracious roaches fatten themselves on enchanted flesh. Any unfortunate who disturbs an infested tomb should keep one eye on cracks in the ground, lest they be buried in seconds.\nThey have toxic bites. It is said that one bite is enough for one to lose an arm.\nIn-game.\nDiablo Immortal.\nTomb Roaches are encountered in the &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They can be found in &lt;a href=\"Ashwold%20Cemetery\"&gt;Ashwold Cemetery&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"the%20Outskirts\"&gt;the Outskirts&lt;/a&gt;; in &lt;a href=\"Shassar%20Sea\"&gt;Shassar Sea&lt;/a&gt; at the three tombs (&lt;a href=\"Chamber%20of%20Sacrifice\"&gt;Chamber of Sacrifice&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chamber%20of%20Truth\"&gt;Chamber of Truth&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chamber%20of%20Wisdom\"&gt;Chamber of Wisdom&lt;/a&gt;) and at &lt;a href=\"Tomb%20of%20Fahir\"&gt;Tomb of Fahir&lt;/a&gt;; in the &lt;a href=\"Library%20of%20Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Library of Zoltun Kulle&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Archive%20of%20Secrets\"&gt;Archive of Secrets&lt;/a&gt;; and on &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Zakarum%20Graveyard\"&gt;Zakarum Graveyard&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey are fragile and attack in swarms of at least five.\nDiablo III.\nTomb Roaches are encountered in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", in &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20the%20Firstborn\"&gt;Temple of the Firstborn&lt;/a&gt;. They are very similar to s in almost every regard.\nThough fragile and weak, Tomb Roaches attack in dozens, encountering less than ten at once is rare. They effectively block the character's pathing and can tie them up for larger foes to come closer. They can also drop from the ceiling, but that will leave them briefly helpless as they try to get back on legs.\nIn battle, they deliver fast bites for average &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; damage.\nVery often, there are bloated corpses around the Temple, each releasing a swarm of Tomb Roaches if approached or touched.\n&lt;a href=\"Wretched%20Host\"&gt;Wretched Host&lt;/a&gt;s seem to be infested by particularly volatile Roaches: they can release a charged-up attack that marks several spots on the ground with green glow. After a few seconds, a swarm of glowing Tomb Roaches will erupt from the Host and explode at the marked areas, dealing heavy &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; damage."}
