{"id": "37491", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37491", "title": "Tomb of Fahir", "text": "The Tomb of Fahir was the final resting place of &lt;a href=\"Fahir\"&gt;Fahir&lt;/a&gt;. It is located in the &lt;a href=\"Shassar%20Sea\"&gt;Shassar Sea&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nThe structure has an inner and outer tomb, along with a treasure room. Many &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;s sought to retrieve the &lt;a href=\"Scepter%20of%20Fahir\"&gt;Scepter of Fahir&lt;/a&gt;, but fell to the tomb's horrors. At some point, a pair of scholars, &lt;a href=\"Rani%20Oran\"&gt;Rani Oran&lt;/a&gt; and her husband entered the tomb, their curiosity overcoming the warnings they'd received. Rani escaped with her life, but her husband did not.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;hero/group of heroes&lt;/a&gt; entered the tomb. Both Fahir and &lt;a href=\"Segithis\"&gt;Segithis&lt;/a&gt; were defeated, and Fahir's part of his scepter retrieved.\nIn-game.\nThe tomb appears as an instanced &lt;a href=\"dungeon%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;dungeon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It appears during the Shassar Sea questline, leading in from \"&lt;a href=\"Fahir%27s%20Legacy\"&gt;Fahir's Legacy&lt;/a&gt;.\" The tomb itself is located west from &lt;a href=\"Sereth%20Outpost\"&gt;Sereth Outpost&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Teargrip\"&gt;Teargrip&lt;/a&gt; drops in this dungeon on &lt;a href=\"Hell%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt; V &lt;a href=\"difficulty\"&gt;difficulty&lt;/a&gt; and above.\nDevelopment.\nOriginally, part of the dungeon involved descending down a rope. This is absent from the final version."}
{"id": "49866", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49866", "title": "Tomb of Hallows", "text": "The Tomb of Hallows is a &lt;a href=\"Kehjistan\"&gt;Kehjistan&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", exclusive to \"&lt;a href=\"Season%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Season of Blood&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nThere is evidence that the tomb may date back to the early days of &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;, to the time of the &lt;a href=\"Ancients\"&gt;Ancients&lt;/a&gt;. Whatever the case, in &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231336\"&gt;1336&lt;/a&gt;, the tomb was (re)appropriated by Lord &lt;a href=\"Zir\"&gt;Zir&lt;/a&gt; and his &lt;a href=\"vampire\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt; cult. &lt;a href=\"Human\"&gt;Human&lt;/a&gt;s were apparently taken into the tomb, their blood drained, before being transferred to &lt;a href=\"Addrine\"&gt;Addrine&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe tomb was stormed by and &lt;a href=\"Erys\"&gt;Erys&lt;/a&gt;. By this point, Zir was apparently aware of their involvement, and had summoned &lt;a href=\"Oren\"&gt;Oren&lt;/a&gt; (his servant) to the tomb, only to be executed. The Wanderer made their way to the tomb's depths where they were able to resist Zir's control and slay the remaining vampires.\nIn-game.\nThe tomb is explored as part of the \"&lt;a href=\"Summons%20of%20the%20Deathless\"&gt;Summons of the Deathless&lt;/a&gt;.\" It is divided into two sections\u2014the Tomb of Hallows itself, and Hallows' End."}
{"id": "26890", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26890", "title": "Tomb of Khan Dakab", "text": "Tomb of Khan Dakab is a one-level dungeon that can be found in &lt;a href=\"Dahlgur%20Oasis\"&gt;Dahlgur Oasis&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Act%20II%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act II&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". Entering the dungeon will start The Lost Treasure of Khan Dakab , which may have a &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; offered to complete it.\nThis dungeon is not guaranteed to appear, but if it does, the entrance will be found within a large sunken ruins area filled with &lt;a href=\"Electric%20Eel\"&gt;Electric Eel&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Serpent%20Magus\"&gt;Serpent Magi&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Copperfang%20Lurkers\"&gt;Copperfang Lurkers&lt;/a&gt;s. To open the door, two levers must be pulled, the first of which will spawn a &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Monsters\"&gt;rare&lt;/a&gt; lurker with &lt;a href=\"minions\"&gt;minions&lt;/a&gt;. A &lt;a href=\"Tomes\"&gt;tome&lt;/a&gt;, \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Chamber%20of%20Faces\"&gt;The Chamber of Faces&lt;/a&gt;\", will be found in an &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Wolf\"&gt;Iron Wolf&lt;/a&gt;'s satchel next to the left-hand lever. Several Iron Wolf corpses are found inside as well.\nThe Tomb itself has multiple randomly generated branches, but is medium in size overall. The goal is to find the lever and open the door to the treasure chamber, which is very close to the entrance. \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Last%20Will%20of%20Khan%20Dakab\"&gt;The Last Will of Khan Dakab&lt;/a&gt;\" is found in a satchel before the door, revealing that Khan Dakab, afraid of his riches bringing bad luck to his family, sealed the door so that no one ever recovers it.\nThe chest within the chamber does not contain loot. Instead, opening it causes four &lt;a href=\"Grim%20Wraith\"&gt;Grim Wraith&lt;/a&gt;s, including the &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20of%20Khan%20Dakab\"&gt;Spirit of Khan Dakab&lt;/a&gt;, to manifest and attack. His spirit drops the usual amount of loot for a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monster\"&gt;Unique Monster&lt;/a&gt;."}
