{"id": "21556", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21556", "title": "Tome of Blacksmithing", "text": "Tomes of Blacksmithing were a type of Pages of Training which were used by the &lt;a href=\"Haedrig%20Eamon\"&gt;Blacksmith&lt;/a&gt; to train and increase the mastery of his craft.\nThey had an &lt;a href=\"Item%20Level\"&gt;Item Level&lt;/a&gt; of 51 and required a character level of 1. They could be stacked up to a maximum of 1000.\n\"\"Give a man a sword and you can make him a warrior. Teach a man to forge and you can raise an army.\" -&lt;a href=\"Griswold\"&gt;Griswold&lt;/a&gt;\"\nTrivia.\nThe description is a reference to the common saying \"give a man a fish and you feed him for a day; teach a man to fish and you feed him for a lifetime\"."}
{"id": "7256", "revid": "493220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7256", "title": "Tome of Identify", "text": "The Tome of Identify is a &lt;a href=\"Tomes\"&gt;tome&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\" that can hold 20 &lt;a href=\"Scroll%20of%20Identify\"&gt;Scrolls of Identify&lt;/a&gt;.\nHaving such a tome would spare 18 slots. Scrolls in the inventory are not added automatically to the tome; it must be dragged manually to it in order to add it.\nUsing up all 20 scrolls will make the tome unusable, but new scrolls can be added to it at any time. Scrolls picked up or bought while the Tome is in the inventory are automatically added to the tome, unless the maximum number has been reached.\nThe Tome functions the same as the Scroll of Identify; Right-clicking it will cause the cursor to change to \"Identify\" mode, and clicking on an Identifiable item will cause it to use up one Scroll, and identify the item.\nLike individual scrolls, the Tome loses its usefulness if the player rescues &lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;Deckard Cain&lt;/a&gt; themselves. Since Cain identifies all items for free if the player retrieves him, it is a better use of gold to buy more Town Portal scrolls for a quick trip back to town."}
{"id": "21557", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21557", "title": "Tome of Jewelcrafting", "text": "Tomes of Jewelcrafting were a type of Pages of Training which are used by the &lt;a href=\"Covetous%20Shen\"&gt;Jeweler&lt;/a&gt; to train and increase the mastery of his craft.\nThey had an &lt;a href=\"Item%20Level\"&gt;Item Level&lt;/a&gt; of 51 and required a &lt;a href=\"Character%20Level\"&gt;Character Level&lt;/a&gt; of 1. They could be stacked up to a maximum of 1000.\nCovetous Shen could craft one Tome of Jewelcrafting at level 6 with 10 &lt;a href=\"gold\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt; and 10 &lt;a href=\"Page%20of%20Jewelcrafting\"&gt;Pages of Jewelcrafting&lt;/a&gt;.\n\"\"Everything one could ever need to know of jewels can be found hidden within the legends of &lt;a href=\"Zei\"&gt;Zei&lt;/a&gt; the trickster.\"\""}
{"id": "21558", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21558", "title": "Tome of Secrets", "text": "Tomes of Secrets were a type of Page of Training which were used by both the &lt;a href=\"Haedrig%20Eamon\"&gt;Blacksmith&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Covetous%20Shen\"&gt;Jeweler&lt;/a&gt; to train their abilities and craft potent items.\nThey had an &lt;a href=\"Item%20Level\"&gt;Item Level&lt;/a&gt; of 61 and required a &lt;a href=\"Character%20Level\"&gt;Character Level&lt;/a&gt; of 1. They could be stacked up to a maximum of 1000.\nCovetous Shen could craft one Tome of Secrets at level 8 with 10 &lt;a href=\"gold\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt; and 10 &lt;a href=\"Tome%20of%20Jewelcrafting\"&gt;Tomes of Jewelcrafting&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe tome would only be dropped on &lt;a href=\"Inferno%20%28Difficulty%29\"&gt;Inferno&lt;/a&gt; difficulty.\n\"Peering at the contents inside causes your head to throb with pain.\""}
{"id": "9497", "revid": "845641", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9497", "title": "Tome of Skill", "text": ""}
{"id": "3739", "revid": "5562046", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3739", "title": "Tome of Town Portal", "text": "The Tome of Town Portal is a &lt;a href=\"Tomes\"&gt;tome&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\" that can hold 20 &lt;a href=\"Scroll%20of%20Town%20Portal\"&gt;Scrolls of Town Portal&lt;/a&gt;.\nHaving such a tome would spare 18 slots. The tome contains three scrolls upon purchase. Scrolls in the inventory are not added automatically to the tome; it must be dragged manually to it in order to add it.\nUsing up all 20 scrolls will make the tome unusable, but new scrolls can be added to it at any time. Scrolls picked up or bought while the Tome is in the inventory are automatically added to the tome, unless the maximum number has been reached.\nRight clicking on the tome will open a &lt;a href=\"Town%20Portal\"&gt;town portal&lt;/a&gt; in the same fashion as a normal scroll."}
{"id": "19524", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19524", "title": "Tome of town portal", "text": ""}
{"id": "5610", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5610", "title": "Tomes", "text": "Tomes are books filled with ancient lore, myth or wisdom. In the &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20series\"&gt;\"Diablo\" series&lt;/a&gt;, tomes can be found throughout the games, often used to fill in extra story and/or lore details.\nDiablo I.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\", there are several tomes to be found within the dark labyrinth beneath &lt;a href=\"Tristram\"&gt;Tristram&lt;/a&gt;. Reading a tome will trigger scrolling text with voiced narration. These tomes are used to trigger quests and/or fill in lore/story details.\nIn addition, &lt;a href=\"Spellbook\"&gt;Spellbook&lt;/a&gt;s can be found throughout the game or bought and used to learn (or augment) various spells and abilities.\nThree extra tomes can be found in \"\". They chronicle a &lt;a href=\"sorcerer\"&gt;sorcerer&lt;/a&gt;'s attempts to control &lt;a href=\"Na-Krul\"&gt;Na-Krul&lt;/a&gt;.\nDiablo II.\nTomes are rarer in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\" than its predecessor. When read however, the text similarly scrolls up across the screen with voiced narration.\nIn Diablo II tomes are also items which can collect magical scrolls. The two types of tomes, &lt;a href=\"Tome%20of%20Town%20Portal\"&gt;Tome of Town Portal&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Tome%20of%20Identify\"&gt;Tome of Identify&lt;/a&gt;, are designed to hold volumes of similar spells, each tome can store up to 20 scrolls of the same type. Vendors who sell scrolls generally sell tomes as well. Right-click on a tome to cast one of the scrolls stored within it. When a tome is empty, it remains in inventory until it is replenished with more scrolls, sold, dropped, or traded. Add scrolls to a tome in your inventory or Stash by dropping the scroll directly onto the tome. Dropping one tome onto another will consolidate both into a single tome, unless the tome being placed has more scrolls than the other tome has room for.\nDiablo Immortal.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", a single 'mega tome' called the &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Bestiary\"&gt;Horadric Bestiary&lt;/a&gt; features. However, there are a few cases of tomes that can be found in the larger world. In most cases, tomes do not exist per se, but rather, pieces of writing (or even illustrations) can be found. The writing is displayed on-screen, then disappears.\nDiablo III.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", tomes are approached differently and indeed, few actual tomes are found in the game. Rather, in the game, short writings can be found across the game's acts, sometimes encompassing different parts of the same overall writing. These tomes are voiced, but appear in a corner of the screen, allowing the player to keep control of their character while listening to/reading the text. Any discovered manuscripts can be accessed at will.\nDiablo IV.\nTomes return in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". They function in a similar manner to \"Diablo III\". Unlike \"Diablo III\" however, tomes are not stored, meaning they cannot be re-read unless the player finds them again in the field. At least in some cases (e.g. s), tomes can be read more than once upon revisiting the area."}
