{"id": "42013", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42013", "title": "Tomi", "text": "Tomi is a former member of the &lt;a href=\"Sand%20Scorpions\"&gt;Sand Scorpions&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, Tomi was part of a Sand Scorpion attack on &lt;a href=\"Sereth%20Outpost\"&gt;Sereth Outpost&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"Amber%20Blades\"&gt;Amber Blades&lt;/a&gt; fought off the attack, causing the Scorpions to retreat, leaving Tomi as the lone straggler. The Blades brought him before &lt;a href=\"Tabri\"&gt;Tabri&lt;/a&gt;, where he begged for his life, telling Tabri that Vataos punished any dissent with execution. Tabri, being a former member of the Scorpions herself, didn't need to be reminded, and offered Tomi a place in the Blades. Tomi accepted, and accompanied Tabri to the &lt;a href=\"Chamber%20of%20Truth\"&gt;Chamber of Truth&lt;/a&gt;, along with the rest of the Blades. Tabri was presented with the reconstituted &lt;a href=\"Scepter%20of%20Fahir\"&gt;Scepter of Fahir&lt;/a&gt;, and declared herself to be the new ruler of Shassar. Tabri and the Blades knelt before her.\nAfter Tabri was lost, the Sand Scorpions began to stir, and increased their activities. Predicting an impending attack on the Amber Blades, &lt;a href=\"Peth\"&gt;Peth&lt;/a&gt; sent Tomi to the Sand Scorpions as a false spy in order to feed them false information and lure them into an ambus. \nIn-game.\nTomi appears in the \"\"&lt;a href=\"Final%20Fragment\"&gt;Final Fragment&lt;/a&gt;\"\" &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". Players can listen in on the conversation he has with Tabri. He later appears in the Chamber of Wisdom. He is also featured in the &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal%20Side%20Quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt;; \"\"&lt;a href=\"Loyalty%20in%20Question\"&gt;Loyalty in Question&lt;/a&gt;\"\"."}
