{"id": "34429", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34429", "title": "Tong-Shi", "text": "Tong-Shi is the father god of the &lt;a href=\"Xian\"&gt;Xian&lt;/a&gt; pantheon. He is believed to be omnipresent but not omniscient. Because of this, he is generally depicted with a somewhat overwhelmed expression.\nA temple dedicated to Tong-Shi exists in &lt;a href=\"Zhou\"&gt;Zhou&lt;/a&gt;. "}
{"id": "44562", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44562", "title": "Tong-Shi's Renewal", "text": "Tong-Shi's Renewal is a festival that originated in &lt;a href=\"Xiansai\"&gt;Xiansai&lt;/a&gt;. It is a time to wish blessings on one another. It is named in honor of/in dedication to &lt;a href=\"Tong-Shi\"&gt;Tong-Shi&lt;/a&gt;; a &lt;a href=\"Xian\"&gt;Xian&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"deity\"&gt;deity&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nTong-Shi's Renewal is a recurring \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" event that corresponds with Lunar New Year. It is currently being held from January 31\u2013February 25, 2024.\nDuring the event, players can complete up to three tasks a day to earn festive rewards, such as &lt;a href=\"Red%20Bag\"&gt;Red Bag&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Tseym\"&gt;Tseym&lt;/a&gt;. Players can also receive rewards such as the Divine Framework of Xiansai Portrait Frame and With a Bang Emoji for logging in on the following days: January 18, January 21, January 22, January 25, January 28, January 29, February 1, February 4, and February 5. If players a login reward for one of these dates, do not worry, they'll be given a &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; to complete which will provide them with the missed reward once finished. Note that missed rewards must be claimed in chronological order."}
