{"id": "16420", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16420", "title": "Toraja", "text": "Toraja is a semi-large city in the eastern lands of &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;. It is featured in &lt;a href=\"Richard%20A.%20Knaak\"&gt;Richard A. Knaak&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Sin%20War%20%28novels%29\"&gt;Sin War (novels)&lt;/a&gt;. \nFeatures.\nThough not comparable to either the magnitude or glory of the regional capital of &lt;a href=\"Kehjan\"&gt;Kehjan&lt;/a&gt; to the east, Toraja had been known far and wide for it's unique sights, catering to pilgrims and inhabitants alike. Beyond its northwestern gate lay a vast, open market. Near the city-center lay centuries-old intricately sculpted gardens where one could admire the spiral trees or the beautiful Falo Blooms. Other buildings of interest included the towering Arena of Klytos, home of the Nirolian Games. \nToraja also housed the second largest Temple of the &lt;a href=\"Triune\"&gt;Triune&lt;/a&gt; (the only larger one being the main temple in Kehjan). \nFate.\nMuch of the city went up in flame as a result of the Triune's efforts to quell the riot. The Temple itself was utterly destroyed by &lt;a href=\"Uldyssian\"&gt;Uldyssian&lt;/a&gt;'s band of followers. "}
