{"id": "27390", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27390", "title": "Torn Soul", "text": "Torn Soul\u00a0was a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Crafting%20Material\"&gt;Legendary Crafting Material&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It has a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0of 1, is\u00a0&lt;a href=\"account%20bound\"&gt;account bound&lt;/a&gt;, and has a maximum stack amount of 1000. It was required to craft the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Living%20Umbral%20Oath\"&gt;Living Umbral Oath&lt;/a&gt; legendary ceremonial knife. As of patch 2.0.6., it no longer drops, and existing Souls can be sold for 50,000 gold.\nIt could only drop from the unique\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Khazra%20Shaman\"&gt;Khazra Shaman&lt;/a&gt;s:\n\"For some obscure reason, &lt;a href=\"Azgar%20%28Khazra%29\"&gt;Azgar&lt;/a&gt;, the wisest of the &lt;a href=\"khazra\"&gt;khazra&lt;/a&gt; shaman, reasoned that the key to defeating &lt;a href=\"Zagraal\"&gt;Zagraal&lt;/a&gt;, their &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;ic betrayer, could only be found in something straddling the worlds of &lt;a href=\"life\"&gt;life&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;. This belief has led all subsequent khazra shaman into an undying obsession over locating such artifacts, though they no longer even know why.\""}
