{"id": "2546", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2546", "title": "Tornado (Diablo II)", "text": "Tornado is a &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\n\"Manipulating the great winds into a fearsome cyclone, the Druid sends this force of destruction into a throng of opponents, crushing into them and leaving devastation in its wake. \"\nGeneral Information.\nLike &lt;a href=\"Twister\"&gt;Twister&lt;/a&gt;, Tornado can be easily spammed. It's best to aim past a monster (similarly to the Barbarian's Whirlwind) rather than click on a monster and cast.\nFor Windy Druids, Tornado is usually set as the left-click skill for its direct damage, while &lt;a href=\"Hurricane\"&gt;Hurricane&lt;/a&gt; is set as the right-click skill. Tornado does physical damage, rather than an elemental type. Therefore, the chances of running into an immune monster are much lower than with other damage types.\nSkill Progression.\nMana Cost: 10"}
{"id": "9196", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9196", "title": "Tornado (Diablo III)", "text": "Tornado\u00a0was a &lt;a href=\"Wizard\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt; skill in early builds of &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;. It would summon a large tornado of energy to damage everything in its path. The wizard could be seen using it in the four pillar room from the wizard gameplay video.\nIn the released version of the game, this skill was reimplemented as &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Twister\"&gt;Energy Twister&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "39066", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39066", "title": "Tornado (Diablo IV)", "text": "Tornado\u00a0is a Spirit Storm skill used by\u00a0\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", based on the &lt;a href=\"Tornado%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;classic spell&lt;/a&gt; of the same name.\nIn-game.\nLike the &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Twister\"&gt;Energy Twister&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", Tornado creates a &lt;a href=\"piercing\"&gt;piercing&lt;/a&gt; vortex that moves randomly (not homing), but in return, can be spammed quickly. Any enemy it reaches will suffer periodic damage with every tick as long as they remain in range.\nUsing this skill will transform the Druid back into Human form."}
{"id": "16897", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16897", "title": "Tornado (magic suffix)", "text": "Tornado is a &lt;a href=\"suffix\"&gt;suffix&lt;/a&gt; that can appear on &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Items\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Items\"&gt;Rare Items&lt;/a&gt;. It provides &lt;a href=\"Charged%20item\"&gt;charges&lt;/a&gt; of the skill &lt;a href=\"Tornado\"&gt;Tornado&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt can start spawning on items at &lt;a href=\"Item%20Level\"&gt;Item Level&lt;/a&gt; 30, but will not be able to spawn on all items until level 60.\nStats.\n\"Can appear on:\" &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Items\"&gt;Magic Items&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Items\"&gt;Rare Items&lt;/a&gt;\n\"Is available on:\" &lt;a href=\"Amulets\"&gt;Amulets&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Circlets\"&gt;Circlets&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Club%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Clubs&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "52610", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52610", "title": "Tornado (monster skill)", "text": "Tornado is a &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; skill not unlike the similar skill used by the various &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Wizard\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt; classes. The monster sends tornado(es) that travel in a straight line(s). The tornado at times can be empowered by &lt;a href=\"elemental%20damage\"&gt;elemental damage&lt;/a&gt;. Tornadoes normally have a small range around themselves from where players are pulled to the center.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", it is used by &lt;a href=\"Sanctifier%20Proxies\"&gt;Sanctifier Proxies&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"the%20Curator\"&gt;the Curator&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dymdrail\"&gt;Dymdrail&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Phangwrth\"&gt;Phangwrth&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Iphael\"&gt;Iphael&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "43338", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43338", "title": "Torr", "text": "Torr is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". He is the father of &lt;a href=\"Navair\"&gt;Navair&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nTorr is a former (likely the previous) chief of &lt;a href=\"Bitter%20Hearth\"&gt;Bitter Hearth&lt;/a&gt; village. He was among the Barbarians that died at the &lt;a href=\"Plains%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Plains of Blood&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231265\"&gt;fall of Arreat&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;Five years later&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;hero/group of heroes&lt;/a&gt; chased a &lt;a href=\"Dravec\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt; with a &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt; shard to the &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Tundra\"&gt;Frozen Tundra&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Arreat\"&gt;Arreat&lt;/a&gt; in order to stop him from giving the shard to a &lt;a href=\"Skarn\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;. Torr was one of the Barbarian spirits the hero(es) asked for their blessings in order to enter the &lt;a href=\"Mbwiru%20Eikura\"&gt;Unformed Land&lt;/a&gt;."}
