{"id": "28700", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=28700", "title": "Tortured Soul", "text": "Tortured Soul, The Doom Scholar is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Thrall\"&gt;Dark Thrall&lt;/a&gt; in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It spawns in &lt;a href=\"The%20Lyceum\"&gt;The Lyceum&lt;/a&gt; as the \"boss\" of the &lt;a href=\"The%20Crumbling%20Tower\"&gt;The Crumbling Tower&lt;/a&gt; event.\nIn combat, it has &lt;a href=\"Electrified\"&gt;Electrified&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Jailer\"&gt;Jailer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Nightmarish\"&gt;Nightmarish&lt;/a&gt; traits.\nTrivia.\nA , after which this monster's zone is named, is an academic institution, specifically a high school in modern Greece or the Aristotelian school of philosophy in ancient Greece. The Tortured Soul's title \"The Doom Scholar\" implies a deeper connection to The Lyceum than simple demonic invasion."}
{"id": "48506", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48506", "title": "Totem", "text": "Totems are devices (normally appearing as intricately carved staffs/statues) employed by &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;-using &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s in the Diablo franchise to various AoE effects. They are treated as monsters in the gameplay. They are temporary, and can be destroyed before they expire.\nTypes.\nAnother variant is the &lt;a href=\"Petrified\"&gt;petrifying&lt;/a&gt; totems used by &lt;a href=\"Gebdu\"&gt;Gebdu&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Gorgothra\"&gt;Gorgothra&lt;/a&gt;."}
