{"id": "50522", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50522", "title": "Tower War", "text": "Tower War is a recurring PvP event in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is currently running from May 8 to June 3, 2024.\nGameplay.\nThe gameplay uses the same format as &lt;a href=\"Conqueror\"&gt;Conqueror&lt;/a&gt;, although some aspects are changed: victory requires 1300 points, and the Sacred Guardian awakens at 800 points.\nLike &lt;a href=\"Battleground\"&gt;Battleground&lt;/a&gt;, Tower War has rankings for the player to climb. Rewards can be earned such as upgrade materials, Legendary items, and Normal Gems. There is also a compensation for AFK players and a protection from losing a major rank.\nFor the duration of the event, Tower War takes place from 10 a.m.\u201312 p.m., 2\u20134 p.m., and 8\u201310 p.m. server time each day of its run. To enter, a player must at least be &lt;a href=\"Character%20Level\"&gt;Level&lt;/a&gt; 46.\nHistory.\nThe rule changes and quality-of-life features similar to Battleground were introduced in the update.\nIn the update, a cooldown was added to the Request Raid Leadership button."}
