{"id": "40808", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40808", "title": "Toxic Lurker", "text": "Toxic Lurkers are a type of &lt;a href=\"spider\"&gt;spider&lt;/a&gt; enemy. They are rare creatures, and their fangs secrete venom, which they use against their prey. However, when controlled in the right dosage, this venom can serve as a life-saving anesthetic.\nDiablo Immortal.\nToxic Lurkers appear in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They are found in the &lt;a href=\"Wortham\"&gt;Wortham&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ashwold%20Cemetery\"&gt;Ashwold Cemetery&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wood\"&gt;Dark Wood&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shassar%20Sea\"&gt;Shassar Sea&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt; zones. They attack by spitting &lt;a href=\"poison\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt; at the player.\nDiablo III.\nToxic Lurkers appear in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". They are the largest (and least numerous) 'warrior' spiders. They are easily seen from afar due to their size, and cannot hide in the webs. Their melee attack hits quite hard, they can launch webs that cover greater areas, and also have innate Plagued affix that allows them to spawn one pool of poison on the ground."}
