{"id": "23055", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23055", "title": "Trade Consortium Council", "text": "The Trade Consortium Council was the ruling council of &lt;a href=\"Caldeum\"&gt;Caldeum&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nThe Council has always been the ruling body of Caldeum, but it gained additional strength after the fall of the &lt;a href=\"Vizjerei\"&gt;Vizjerei&lt;/a&gt;, in the aftermath of the &lt;a href=\"Mage%20Clan%20Wars\"&gt;Mage Clan Wars&lt;/a&gt;. The councilmen saw opportunity in the rapidly growing &lt;a href=\"Zakarum\"&gt;Zakarum&lt;/a&gt; faith, and allowed the construction of the &lt;a href=\"Saldencal\"&gt;Saldencal&lt;/a&gt; within Caldeum. Not content to reign supreme in commerce and religion, the Council aspired to make Caldeum a nexus of learning as well. It proposed to unite the &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt; academics in a massive new structure - the &lt;a href=\"Yshari%20Sanctum\"&gt;Yshari Sanctum&lt;/a&gt; - which long remained a beacon of learning.\nCircumstances changed with the downfall of &lt;a href=\"Kurast\"&gt;Kurast&lt;/a&gt;, where nobles from the city fled to Caldeum. While initially greatful for the sanctuary the city provided, their relief turned to arrogance, as they began to demand their \"rightful\" place on the Council, and were prepared to hire mercenaries to see their ambition through. Emperor &lt;a href=\"Hakan%20I\"&gt;Hakan I&lt;/a&gt; stepped in and managed to resolve the issue. However, when his successor, &lt;a href=\"Hakan%20II\"&gt;Hakan II&lt;/a&gt; took the throne, Caldeum fell into decline."}
