{"id": "26444", "revid": "25771421", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26444", "title": "Trag'Oul Coils", "text": "Trag'Oul Coils\u00a0are\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0bracers in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". They require\u00a0&lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt;\u00a070 to drop.\nAs of patch 2.4.2, it gained a new legendary affix: &lt;a href=\"Spike%20Trap\"&gt;Spike Trap&lt;/a&gt;s gain the Impaling Spines rune (in addition to any other) and are deployed twice as fast. The latter property means that &lt;a href=\"attack%20speed\"&gt;attack speed&lt;/a&gt; is doubled for this spell (though only for casting purposes, not for damage).\nThis effect has most impact on the Scatter rune, as it effectively quads the damage output compared to the unmodified skill.\nDespite the name, they are not related to &lt;a href=\"Trag%27Oul%27s%20Avatar\"&gt;Trag'Oul's Avatar&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"set\"&gt;set&lt;/a&gt;.\nDevelopment.\nPrior to patch 2.4.2, the unique affix instead allowed replenishing all resources and reducing all \"remaining\" &lt;a href=\"cooldown\"&gt;cooldown&lt;/a&gt;s by 45-60 seconds in addition to regaining &lt;a href=\"Life\"&gt;Life&lt;/a&gt; whenever a player used a &lt;a href=\"Healing%20Well\"&gt;Healing Well&lt;/a&gt; (\"not\" a &lt;a href=\"Pool%20of%20Reflection\"&gt;Pool of Reflection&lt;/a&gt;). Builds relying on long-recharging skills like &lt;a href=\"Archon\"&gt;Archon&lt;/a&gt; could carry these bracers with them in the inventory, equipping those before using a well.\nDue to the way &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Trials\"&gt;Realm of Trials&lt;/a&gt; worked before being removed, these bracers were very effective for builds with long cooldown skills, as those usually had trouble taking out multiple monster waves in a row."}
