{"id": "2420", "revid": "1687225", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2420", "title": "Trang-Oul's Avatar", "text": "Trang-Oul's Avatar is a in \"\".\nThis set is designed for the &lt;a href=\"Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt;, however, any &lt;a href=\"Classes\"&gt;class&lt;/a&gt; can equip the &lt;a href=\"items\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt; in this set, except for . Only the &lt;a href=\"Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; can complete this set.\nIf you complete this set, the &lt;a href=\"Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; will transform into a &lt;a href=\"Vampire\"&gt;Vampire&lt;/a&gt; in appearance. He will also get &lt;a href=\"Skill%20Trees\"&gt;skills&lt;/a&gt; such as , , and &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Ball\"&gt;Fire Ball&lt;/a&gt;. This set certainly allows the wearer to have some fun confusing less experienced players.\nThere is a known bug associated with wearing this set which will increase casting delay, resulting in slower casting (even with &lt;a href=\"Faster%20Cast%20Rate\"&gt;faster cast&lt;/a&gt;-items). While crippling for &lt;a href=\"Bonemancer\"&gt;Bonemancer&lt;/a&gt;, and, to a lesser extent, &lt;a href=\"Novamancer\"&gt;Novamancer&lt;/a&gt; (due to poison damage being applied over time) builds that heavily rely on casting spells, it does not affect &lt;a href=\"Summonmancer\"&gt;Summoners&lt;/a&gt; to a large extent, which rely on minions and only occasionally cast &lt;a href=\"curses\"&gt;curses&lt;/a&gt;.\n\"&lt;a href=\"Trang-Oul\"&gt;Trang-Oul&lt;/a&gt;'s\" is the proper name for this set despite what the manual might say or other spellings seen.\nSet.\n (2 Items)*\n (2 Items)\n (3 Items)\n (3 Items)\n (4 Items)\n (4 Items)\nTrivia.\nThe Vampire\u00a0&lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; is\u00a0an evolution of the &lt;a href=\"Lich\"&gt;Lich&lt;/a&gt; which appeared in Sierra's Hellfire expansion of the original Diablo game. As a Lich is a wizard that deliberately made themselves undead in a quest to gain greater magical powers, it would be a more apropos name for the creature which the Necromancer becomes upon completion of the Trang-Oul set."}
{"id": "5908", "revid": "1687225", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5908", "title": "Trang-Oul's Claws", "text": "Trang-Oul's Claws are &lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;set&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Bracers\"&gt;heavy bracers&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". They are one of the five pieces of the &lt;a href=\"Trang-Oul%27s%20Avatar\"&gt;Trang-Oul's Avatar&lt;/a&gt; item set.\nHighly popular among players that specialize in poisonous skills, this item is favored because of the large bonus it grants to poison skill damage. It's also one of the best-in-slot options for all caster builds such as &lt;a href=\"Wind%20Druid\"&gt;Wind Druid&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Hammerdin\"&gt;Hammerdin&lt;/a&gt;s due to its bonus to &lt;a href=\"Faster%20Cast%20Rate\"&gt;Cast Rate&lt;/a&gt;, a trait that is shared only with the unique light gauntlets, . Trang-Oul's Claws is superior to Magefist for casters that already have a high amount of mana and do not use fire skills, thanks to its large increase to cold resistance.\nStats.\nDefense: \nRequired Level: 45\nRequired &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;: 58\nDurability: 16"}
{"id": "5907", "revid": "1687225", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5907", "title": "Trang-Oul's Girth", "text": "Trang-Oul's Girth is a &lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;set&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Troll%20Belt\"&gt;troll belt&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". It is one of the five pieces of the &lt;a href=\"Trang-Oul%27s%20Avatar\"&gt;Trang-Oul's Avatar&lt;/a&gt; item set. It is a highly useful belt on its own, thanks to its rare &lt;a href=\"Cannot%20be%20Frozen\"&gt;Cannot be Frozen&lt;/a&gt; attribute, on top of its big increases to life, mana, and (with two other set pieces) a huge increase to cold resistance.\nStats.\nDefense: (varies) (Base Defense: 59-66)\nRequired Level: 62\nRequired &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;: \nDurability: 18\n16 Boxes\n (varies)\n (varies)\n (3 Items)"}
{"id": "5904", "revid": "1687225", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5904", "title": "Trang-Oul's Guise", "text": "Trang-Oul's Guise is a &lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;set&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bone%20Visage\"&gt;bone visage&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". It is one of the five pieces of the &lt;a href=\"Trang-Oul%27s%20Avatar\"&gt;Trang-Oul's Avatar&lt;/a&gt; item set. Despite its rarity thanks to its high treasure class, Trang-Oul's Guise is a thoroughly mediocre helmet, with no resistances, +skills or faster cast rate. Unfortunately, wearing it is a concession one needs to make if they wish to have the full set bonuses.\nStats.\nDefense: (varies) (Base Defense: 100-157)\nRequired Level: 65\nRequired &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;: 106\nDurability: 40\n (varies)"}
