{"id": "10045", "revid": "5207274", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10045", "title": "Tremain the Priest", "text": "Tremain the Priest existed in pre-release versions of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\", and is not present in the final version of the game. He originally triggered the quest \"&lt;a href=\"Archbishop%20Lazarus%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Archbishop Lazarus&lt;/a&gt;\". \nTremain also had his own quest, \"Fleshdoom, Wielder of Shadowfang\", where the player was tasked into killing said demon and retrieving the sword Shadowfang, to be destroyed by the priest's holy powers. However, when the player returned the demonblade to Tremain, he was to be consumed by hellfire and slain, with his soul presumably being trapped within the ebon blade. The quest was also was also cut from the game.\nPersonality and Traits.\nTremain was a kind and just man, known for his many talents. As holy man from an Ancient Order (presumably a &lt;a href=\"Zakarum\"&gt;Zakarum&lt;/a&gt;), he was a wielder of light, capable of both healing the wounded and also performing powerful exorcisms, as he seen by his ability to purge evil from the man who was possessed by the demon Fleshdoom. Tremain was admired and revered by the townsfolk of Tristram, particularly Pepin, who learned a lot from the priest.\nWhile not a fighter himself, Tremain was supposedly powerful enough to hold himself against demons, as noted by him mentioning he was able to fight Fleshdoom before the demon fled into The Labyrinth beneath the &lt;a href=\"Tristram%20Cathedral\"&gt;cathedral&lt;/a&gt;. Tremain was also able to wander in and out of Tristram without being targeted by the cloaked riders, who were the demonic entities that would attack any villager who tried to leave the town. &lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;Deckard Cain&lt;/a&gt; noted that Tremain's ability to travel with little problems aided the Tristram in keeping some contact with the rest of the &lt;a href=\"Khanduras\"&gt;kingdom&lt;/a&gt;.\nDespite his holy powers of exorcism, even Tremain was unable to purge the evil from the demonblade Shadowfang, which ultimately led to his demise."}
{"id": "16474", "revid": "99965", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16474", "title": "Tremas", "text": "Tremas was a master huntsman in life. His skill as a huntsman and archer was only surpassed - eventually - by his son, &lt;a href=\"Achilios\"&gt;Achilios&lt;/a&gt;. \nTremas carved the large huntingbow that Achilios inherited from his father; a mighty weapon that few other than Achilios or Tremas could manage to string. &lt;a href=\"Uldyssian\"&gt;Uldyssian&lt;/a&gt; suspected that Achilios's and Tremas's great skills might have been augmented by a similar magic he now wielded."}
