{"id": "50703", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50703", "title": "Triage", "text": "Triage is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" in which a medical camp must be defended from a demon attack. It takes place on &lt;a href=\"The%20Battlefields\"&gt;The Battlefields&lt;/a&gt; of , where a &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; may be offered to complete it.\nThe event begins by speaking with Sergeant Brooks, who believes he has secured his fortified camp. He arrogantly rejects &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt;'s assistance, but nearby Nurse Melana is happy to request &lt;a href=\"the%20Nephalem\"&gt;the Nephalem&lt;/a&gt;'s aid as Brooks is promptly snatched up by a &lt;a href=\"Winged%20Molok\"&gt;Winged Molok&lt;/a&gt;. The rest of the Molok swarm lands and must be killed, earning a brief lull in the fighting. It is ended as the wounded &lt;a href=\"Bastion%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Bastion's Keep&lt;/a&gt; guards feel a rumbling below, followed by a pack of &lt;a href=\"Heralds%20of%20Pestilence\"&gt;Heralds of Pestilence&lt;/a&gt; emerging, including the &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Handible\"&gt;Handible&lt;/a&gt;. After all monsters are dead, speaking with a grateful Melana completes the event, awarding gold and experience.\nThis event is similar to &lt;a href=\"Tide%20of%20Battle\"&gt;Tide of Battle&lt;/a&gt;, both taking place in a lightly fortified camp somewhere on the battlefield. The two events appear to be mutually exclusive within a given game.\nTrivia.\n is a process in medical care to determine a priority for treating a large number of patients, sometimes including situations in battle. With limited resources, triage sometimes means allowing a critically injured patient to die in order to save others. In this event, The Nephalem protects most of the medical camp, but is unable to save Sergeant Brooks."}
{"id": "52307", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52307", "title": "Trial Chamber", "text": "The is one of the chambers featured in \"&lt;a href=\"Kulle%27s%20Hidden%20Chambers\"&gt;Kulle's Hidden Chambers&lt;/a&gt;\" in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGameplay.\nThe player is greeted by the Echo of Kulle, who gives them a trial. A treasure chest is awarded for completing the trial. The trial is to defeat the three waves of &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s it summons."}
{"id": "53347", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53347", "title": "Trial of Mists", "text": "The Trial of Mists is a &lt;a href=\"Spiritborn\"&gt;Spiritborn&lt;/a&gt; ritual.\nAs children, prospective Spiritborn are sent into the jungle of &lt;a href=\"Nahantu\"&gt;Nahantu&lt;/a&gt; to be judged by the spirits. Only a few are deemed worthy to become Spiritborn, and those who are not called by the Spirit Guardians are culled. The chosen children are granted power beyond compare through their unbreakable bonds with the &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Guardians\"&gt;Spirit Guardians&lt;/a&gt;, and have a sacred charge to wield their power well. The culling itself is apparently carried out by lesser spirits who serve the Spirit Guardians."}
