{"id": "47298", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47298", "title": "Trial of the Hordes", "text": " is a recurring limited time competitive PvE event in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". The player has to complete the &lt;a href=\"Trial%20of%20the%20Hordes%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;quest with the same name&lt;/a&gt; to unlock this event. It is currently running from July 19, 3 a.m.\u2013July 26, 3 a.m. server time, 2024.\nGameplay.\nPlayers don't fight against each other; instead they compete for the best performance in fighting against &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s. The winner is decided by who lasted longest or killed more monsters by the timeout. Players rank up by scoring points and receive rewards at the end of the season based on their ranking. The following additional rewards are available:\nRank rewards.\nThe rank rewards are received at the end of the season based on the player's final rank.\nHistory.\nTrial of the Hordes was first available from June 28, 3 a.m\u2013July 12, 3 a.m (server time).\nTrial of Plunder.\nDuring &lt;a href=\"March%20of%20the%20Goblins\"&gt;March of the Goblins&lt;/a&gt;, a version of Trial of the Hordes called Trial of Plunder was active. This version replaced many of the enemies with &lt;a href=\"Treasure%20Goblin\"&gt;Treasure Goblin&lt;/a&gt;s, which dropped multiple stacks of 1 gold each. The \"Perdition\" boss monster also didn't spawn, making it more likely to reach high kill streaks and the match ending with a timeout instead of one of the players being killed."}
