{"id": "4978", "revid": "1687225", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4978", "title": "Troll Nest", "text": "Troll Nests are the &lt;a href=\"Elite%20Items\"&gt;elite&lt;/a&gt; versions of s. They offer the best defense out of any light shields in the game, and have fairly low strength requirements for elite gear. Their only downside is their maximum socket limit of 3, meaning that they cannot be made into the 4-rune runewords: &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Rune%20Word\"&gt;Spirit&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Phoenix%20Rune%20Word\"&gt;Phoenix&lt;/a&gt;. This is a significant drawback because Spirit in particular is one of the cheapest and most powerful runewords available.\nStats.\nDefense: 158-173\nLevel Requirement: 57\nStrength Requirement: 106\nChance to Block: (&lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt;) / (&lt;a href=\"Amazon\"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Assassin\"&gt;Assassin&lt;/a&gt;, ) / (&lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Sorceress\"&gt;Sorceress&lt;/a&gt;)\nDurability: 74\nSockets: 3\n&lt;a href=\"Smite\"&gt;Smite&lt;/a&gt; Damage: 24-38\nType: Light\nQuality Level: 76"}
