{"id": "43967", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43967", "title": "Trond", "text": "Trond is a of the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Wolf%20Tribe\"&gt;Shadow Wolf Tribe&lt;/a&gt;. He lives at &lt;a href=\"Bitter%20Hearth\"&gt;Bitter Hearth&lt;/a&gt; village.\nBiography.\nTrond possessed the &lt;a href=\"Tempest%20Stone\"&gt;Tempest Stone&lt;/a&gt;, as possessed by his father, and his father before him. However, in &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, while on the &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Tundra\"&gt;Frozen Tundra&lt;/a&gt;, the stone was stolen by a &lt;a href=\"Tempest%20Stone%20Thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt;, who left Trond temporarily incapacitated. Trond requested aid from an &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt; to retrieve the relic, which they did. The adventurer informed Trond that the thief had met his end, and handed the stone back, hoping Trond avoided the same fate.\nLater Trond spotted an &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Clan\"&gt;Ice Clan&lt;/a&gt; Shaman leading &lt;a href=\"yeti\"&gt;yeti&lt;/a&gt; around like an experienced &lt;a href=\"druid\"&gt;druid&lt;/a&gt;. In his curiosity he went to investigate but was captured and trapped behind a wall of &lt;a href=\"ice\"&gt;ice&lt;/a&gt;. Luckily an &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt; saw him. Trond could not be freed because the ice wall was reinforced by &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;. Attempting to break the wall caused a ruckus that brought the &lt;a href=\"Zhaturr\"&gt;shaman&lt;/a&gt; back. Fortunately for Trond the &lt;a href=\"Khazra%20Shaman\"&gt;Khazra Shaman&lt;/a&gt; didn't have a firm control of the yeti, and one of them broke the wall in its rampage.\nLater, &lt;a href=\"Bitter%20Hearth\"&gt;Bitter Hearth&lt;/a&gt; was hit by a heavy blizzard. Trond helped to build a windbreak.\nWhen &lt;a href=\"Fianne\"&gt;Fianne&lt;/a&gt; gathered barbarians to rebuild &lt;a href=\"Sescheron\"&gt;Sescheron&lt;/a&gt;, Trond volunteered. His duty was to plant cedars, upon which the names of those that died in &lt;a href=\"Harrogath\"&gt;Harrogath&lt;/a&gt; would be carved on.\nIn-game.\nTrond is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". He appears in &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Tundra\"&gt;Frozen Tundra&lt;/a&gt;, in the \"&lt;a href=\"Heart%20of%20the%20Storm\"&gt;Heart of the Storm&lt;/a&gt;\", \"&lt;a href=\"Overgrowth\"&gt;Overgrowth&lt;/a&gt;\", and \"&lt;a href=\"Unusual%20Cold\"&gt;Unusual Cold&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal%20Side%20Quests\"&gt;side quests&lt;/a&gt;. He dual wields tomahawks to fight."}
{"id": "50864", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50864", "title": "Trophies (Diablo Immortal)", "text": "Trophies were added to \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" in the &lt;a href=\"Precipice%20of%20Horror\"&gt;Precipice of Horror&lt;/a&gt; update.\nCompleting a Trophy records the date that the rewards were claimed on the Trophies page.\nList of Trophies.\nLegacy.\nTrophies in this category can no longer be obtained, but the Codex keeps the record of when they were completed, also allowing the reward to be claimed on the off chance that the player completed the challenge but didn't claim the reward.\nTrophy Points.\nTrophy Points are earned by claiming Trophies. Reaching certain numbers of Trophy Points allows claiming of rewards:\nHistory.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Unending%20Storm\"&gt;Unending Storm&lt;/a&gt; update, &lt;a href=\"Difficulty%23Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;difficulties&lt;/a&gt; were changed and the trophies referencing them were updated to match. Some &lt;a href=\"Helliquary\"&gt;Helliquary&lt;/a&gt; bosses were retired and their trophies were moved into the Legacy category - interestingly, their description was also updated to say \"Hell I\" even though it was never possible to challenge them at that difficulty after the update. Also Apothrus' trophy kept the \"or higher\" in the description, despite him being restricted to the Hell I difficulty. In the same update, the &lt;a href=\"Challenge%20Rift%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;Challenge Rift&lt;/a&gt; trophies had their thresholds updated from 100-200-300-400-500 to 40-80-120-150-180.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20Manifest\"&gt;Nightmare Manifest&lt;/a&gt; update introduced new Trophies for Runes, Duels, the new Age of Unmaking events and Helliquary bosses, as well as \"have a Tempest as a friend\". The \"Age of Unmaking\" section was renamed to \"Abyssal Verge\", even though the trophies related to Terror Rifts, Oblivion Pillars and Hellslayer Bounties are still in this section."}
