{"id": "46799", "revid": "1687225", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46799", "title": "Hearth Rune Word", "text": "Hearth is the &lt;a href=\"Rune%20Word\"&gt;rune word&lt;/a&gt; \" for &lt;a href=\"helms\"&gt;helms&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". It is &lt;a href=\"Ladder\"&gt;Ladder&lt;/a&gt; only.\nHearth is an easily made helmet and can be equipped at early-mid levels. It provides a solid array defensive of bonuses, mostly geared at making its wearer less susceptible to cold.\nHearth is the cold variant of the patch 2.6 rune words, and is analogous to the &lt;a href=\"Fire\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt;-oriented &lt;a href=\"Temper%20Rune%20Word\"&gt;Temper Rune Word&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt;-oriented &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Rune%20Word\"&gt;Cure Rune Word&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lightning\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt;-oriented &lt;a href=\"Ground%20Rune%20Word\"&gt;Ground Rune Word&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt;-oriented &lt;a href=\"Bulwark%20Rune%20Word\"&gt;Bulwark Rune Word&lt;/a&gt;. Cold damage is not as common or as threatening as lightning or fire damage, but the &lt;a href=\"Cannot%20be%20Frozen\"&gt;Cannot be Frozen&lt;/a&gt; mod is very valuable, and much easier to obtain with this rune word than rare and expensive options such as &lt;a href=\"Raven%20Frost\"&gt;Raven Frost&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Kira%27s%20Guardian\"&gt;Kira's Guardian&lt;/a&gt;.\nResult:"}
{"id": "47065", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47065", "title": "Hearthrot", "text": "The Hearthrot is a group of &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s that invaded &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;, some time after the &lt;a href=\"Terror%27s%20Tide\"&gt;Siege of Stormpoint&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nc. &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231272\"&gt;1272&lt;/a&gt;, the Hearthrot emerged from different parts of Sanctuary. The earth was rent in large &lt;a href=\"cracks\"&gt;fissures&lt;/a&gt; at the points of their emergence. The fissures vented demonic energy which corrupted the surrounding &lt;a href=\"animal\"&gt;wildlife&lt;/a&gt;, and even affected the environment. From there, they moved to different regions, and made lairs in locations that fit their tastes, and from there enacted to make their desires for Sanctuary a reality.\nTheir actions did not go unnoticed. &lt;a href=\"Rayek\"&gt;Rayek&lt;/a&gt; had just made an altar that improved the &lt;a href=\"Helliquary\"&gt;Helliquary&lt;/a&gt;'s range. The Helliquary picked up a disturbance originating from &lt;a href=\"Saarodan%2C%20Sky-Sunderer\"&gt;Saarodan's&lt;/a&gt; fissure. After &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; investigated the disturbance, they discovered the Hearthrot. The Shard-seeker was sent to seal the demonic energy released by the Hearthrot's emergence. After that, they tracked the demons to their lairs where they were defeated, and their body parts sealed in the Helliquary.\nIn-game.\nThe Hearthrot is the third set of &lt;a href=\"Helliquary\"&gt;Helliquary&lt;/a&gt; bosses in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They are unlocked by completing the prologue &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal%20quests\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;, \"&lt;a href=\"Hearthrot%20Helliquary\"&gt;Hearthrot Helliquary&lt;/a&gt;\", and unlocking II &lt;a href=\"difficulty\"&gt;difficulty&lt;/a&gt;."}
