{"id": "3060", "revid": "44564686", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3060", "title": "Hell (difficulty)", "text": "Hell is a &lt;a href=\"difficulty\"&gt;difficulty&lt;/a&gt; level, following in the &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20series\"&gt;\"Diablo\"&lt;/a&gt; series. \nDiablo I.\nMuch like Nightmare, Hell Difficulty is present in Diablo's multiplayer, as well as all of \"&lt;a href=\"Hellfire\"&gt;Hellfire&lt;/a&gt;\". Both have varying changes, but a list below compiles changes seen in both cases:\nDiablo II.\nThe complete list of the effects of Hell include:\nFor having access to the Hell difficulty the following requirements must be met:\nHell difficulty is the only difficulty level in which the two &lt;a href=\"Battle.net\"&gt;Battle.net&lt;/a&gt; only quests, the &lt;a href=\"Pandemonium%20Event\"&gt;Pandemonium Event&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Uber%20Diablo\"&gt;Uber Diablo&lt;/a&gt; Quest can be obtained.\nIf a character accomplished the last Quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Harrowing\"&gt;Act IV&lt;/a&gt; (killing Diablo) in non-expansion you will gain a new &lt;a href=\"Titles\"&gt;title&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf it is an expansion character, you must kill Baal in &lt;a href=\"Lord%20of%20Destruction%20%28Act%29\"&gt;Act V&lt;/a&gt; to gain a new title.\nDiablo Immortal.\nHell difficulty forms the majority of difficulties in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". Originally, Hell difficulty was unlocked when &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 60 is reached, at which point the player gains access to &lt;a href=\"Paragon\"&gt;Paragon&lt;/a&gt; levels. As of the &lt;a href=\"Terror%27s%20Tide\"&gt;Terror's Tide&lt;/a&gt; update, Hell difficulties are tied to defeating Helliquary bosses.\nFor details on difficulties in this game, see &lt;a href=\"Difficulty%23Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Difficulty#Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "44064", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44064", "title": "Hell Beasts", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;Realm of Damnation&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\n\"&lt;a href=\"Bitter%20Hearth\"&gt;Bitter Hearth&lt;/a&gt; is no stranger to &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s, but as of late we are being overrun by hell-beasts. There is a rumor that a gate to &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt; has been opened within the depths of &lt;a href=\"Sescheron\"&gt;Sescheron&lt;/a&gt;, and it is from here that these demon-beasts have found their way to us. I care not how you do it. I just ask that you thin out these beasts before they reach my &lt;a href=\"Children%20of%20Bul-Kathos\"&gt;people&lt;/a&gt;.\""}
{"id": "8992", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8992", "title": "Hell Boar", "text": "The Hell Boar is a great humanoid &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; and one of the many followers of &lt;a href=\"Na-Krul\"&gt;Na-Krul&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". This monster appears in the &lt;a href=\"Festering%20Nest\"&gt;Festering Nest&lt;/a&gt;. It is a large monster that uses its great tusks to gouge at the adventurer, and can be quite troublesome in numbers. \nThey have an ability to knockback with their attacks."}
{"id": "7253", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7253", "title": "Hell Bovine", "text": "Hell Bovines are bipedal cattle with &lt;a href=\"polearms\"&gt;polearms&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nGiven sentience by &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt; and driven mad by the incessant prodding they suffered at the hands of the &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo\"&gt;heroes&lt;/a&gt; that swarmed to &lt;a href=\"Tristram\"&gt;Tristram&lt;/a&gt;, these hell-spawned bovines sought to destroy those who abused them when they were docile and defenseless. Armed with vicious halberds, they lay in wait just on the other side of a secret portal that was opened with the \"help\" of their &lt;a href=\"Wirt\"&gt;first victim&lt;/a&gt;...\nIn-game.\nHell Bovines are only found in the &lt;a href=\"Secret%20Cow%20Level\"&gt;Secret Cow Level&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\", accessible only after finishing the game on &lt;a href=\"Normal\"&gt;Normal&lt;/a&gt; difficulty and transmuting together a &lt;a href=\"Tome%20of%20Town%20Portal\"&gt;Tome of Town Portal&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Wirt%27s%20Leg\"&gt;Wirt's Leg&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Cube\"&gt;Horadric Cube&lt;/a&gt;, inside the &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Encampment\"&gt;Rogue Encampment&lt;/a&gt;.\nHell Bovines are burdened with slow foot speed, but they hit quite hard, and mass in huge herds, making them potentially dangerous to melee characters or ranged attackers who are not careful to maintain their distance. When fighting these animals, do not run wildly as that will gather more groups of Hell Bovines into a huge mob."}
{"id": "29405", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29405", "title": "Hell Bringer", "text": "Hell Bringers are a form of demonic structure found mostly in the &lt;a href=\"Fields%20of%20Slaughter\"&gt;Fields of Slaughter&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Arreat%20Crater\"&gt;Arreat Crater&lt;/a&gt; and other zones in . They are often located in the middle of rings or triangles of demonic &lt;a href=\"Traps\"&gt;Mine Fields&lt;/a&gt;, or amidst hidden &lt;a href=\"Tormented%20Stinger\"&gt;Tormented Stinger&lt;/a&gt;s.\nThey serve as battlefield fortifications for the &lt;a href=\"Army%20of%20Sin\"&gt;Army of Sin&lt;/a&gt;. When the enemy comes close enough (roughly 40 yards), they release long tentacles to grab the target and pull it close to itself (often into minefields) with a small delay. When the enemy is very close, they can also produce flames to cause &lt;a href=\"fire%20damage\"&gt;fire damage&lt;/a&gt; in a small radius to the player.\nWhile Hell Bringers count as enemies, and even give &lt;a href=\"experience\"&gt;experience&lt;/a&gt; upon destruction, they drop no loot."}
