{"id": "4424", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4424", "title": "Hell Forge Hammer", "text": "The Hell Forge Hammer (also spelt Hellforge Hammer) is a hammer once used by &lt;a href=\"Hephasto\"&gt;Hephasto&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nThe hammer was used by Hephasto upon the &lt;a href=\"Anvil%20of%20Annihilation\"&gt;Anvil of Annihilation&lt;/a&gt;, where he forged countless weapons. It had the power to even shatter &lt;a href=\"soulstone\"&gt;soulstone&lt;/a&gt;s, which it was used to do so by a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20II\"&gt;group of heroes&lt;/a&gt;, who destroyed the soulstones of &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mephisto\"&gt;Mephisto&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThe Hell Forge hammer is a quest item used in the \"&lt;a href=\"Hell%27s%20Forge\"&gt;Hell's Forge&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\", where the player must destroy &lt;a href=\"Mephisto%27s%20Soulstone\"&gt;Mephisto's Soulstone&lt;/a&gt; on the &lt;a href=\"Hellforge\"&gt;Hellforge&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe hammer can also be used as a weapon. It's not very useful compared to the damage of other melee weapons by the time most characters are up to Act IV, but because it has no requirements, it's a popular weapon for people to give to their brand new level 1 characters.\nStats.\nOne-Hand Damage: 6 to 15\nDurability: 55 of 55\nMace Class - Fast Attack Speed\nOther Versions.\nPossibly due to a coding oversight, it may also be possible to alter it better by &lt;a href=\"imbuing\"&gt;imbuing&lt;/a&gt; it or &lt;a href=\"socket\"&gt;socket&lt;/a&gt;ing it with a &lt;a href=\"rune%20word\"&gt;rune word&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "40138", "revid": "1845703", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40138", "title": "Hell Horror", "text": "Hell Horrors are a &lt;a href=\"Skeleton\"&gt;Skeleton&lt;/a&gt; type enemy. \nDiablo I.\nHell Horrors are a &lt;a href=\"Skeleton\"&gt;Skeleton&lt;/a&gt; type enemy that appear only in the PlayStation version of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo I&lt;/a&gt;\". They are found on &lt;a href=\"Level%2016%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Level 16&lt;/a&gt;, taking the place of the &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Knight%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Blood Knights&lt;/a&gt; found in the PC version. &lt;a href=\"Sir%20Gorash\"&gt;Sir Gorash&lt;/a&gt; also appears as a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; Hell Horror in this version of the game.\nDiablo II.\nHell Horrors are a cut sixth skeleton type which was not included in the final version of the game. They were supposed to appear somewhere in &lt;a href=\"Act%20IV\"&gt;Act IV&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Awakening and Diablerie has a Hell Horror after Horror and there is an unused color palette for the skeleton that looks like a red Horror. It's unknown if they would have &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Archer\"&gt;Archers&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Mage\"&gt;Mages&lt;/a&gt;."}
