{"id": "44083", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44083", "title": "Hell Portal", "text": "Hell Portals are &lt;a href=\"portal\"&gt;portal&lt;/a&gt;s linking a location on &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; to another in the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Burning Hells&lt;/a&gt;, or one Hell realm to another. They are characterized by the corrupted growths around them (for permanent portals only), and their burning edges. They can be closed (at least the temporary ones) by &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;mortal&lt;/a&gt; hands.\nIn-game.\nDiablo Immortal.\nHell Portals replace Infernal Gates from \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\" in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;.\" Permanent portals serve as the entrances to the &lt;a href=\"Domain%20of%20Horror\"&gt;Domain of Horror&lt;/a&gt;, and the entrance to the &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;Realm of Damnation&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Ruins%20of%20Sescheron\"&gt;Ruins of Sescheron&lt;/a&gt; that &lt;a href=\"Skarn\"&gt;Skarn&lt;/a&gt; created. Temporary Hell Portals called \"Infernal Hollows\" serve as the entrance to hidden &lt;a href=\"dungeon\"&gt;dungeon&lt;/a&gt;s in the &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Tundra\"&gt;Frozen Tundra&lt;/a&gt;, Realm of Damnation, and &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint\"&gt;Stormpoint&lt;/a&gt;.\nDiablo IV.\nHell Portals will appear in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\" during \"&lt;a href=\"Season%20of%20Hatred%20Rising\"&gt;Season of Hatred Rising&lt;/a&gt;\". Players must defeat &lt;a href=\"Realmwalker\"&gt;Realmwalker&lt;/a&gt;s in order to access them. The portals lead to \"pocket realms\" of Hatred, where, if players complete the zone, will be offered rewards. A &lt;a href=\"Seething%20Opal\"&gt;Seething Opal&lt;/a&gt; will always drop in such cases."}
{"id": "43145", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43145", "title": "Hell Rider", "text": "Hell Riders are a type of &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; seen in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nWhen the &lt;a href=\"Lord%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;Lord of Damnation&lt;/a&gt; notices his servitors working effectively together, he ensures they remain so. A shackled rider and mount are eternally conjoined, granting the resultant being the agility of two wills and the ability to deliver vicious dual strikes in flight.\nIn-game.\nThey can be found at the &lt;a href=\"Halls%20of%20Punishment\"&gt;Halls of Punishment&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Citadel%20of%20the%20Damned\"&gt;Citadel of the Damned&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;Realm of Damnation&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey are also encountered in &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt; during the \"&lt;a href=\"Opening%20the%20Helliquary\"&gt;Opening the Helliquary&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"\" &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;s.\nThe rider-half is an emaciated &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20Servitor\"&gt;Ashen Servitor&lt;/a&gt;, fused to another servitor which has been transformed into a large, bat-like creature. They attack from range; with the rider using a &lt;a href=\"sonic\"&gt;sonic&lt;/a&gt; attack, and the mount using &lt;a href=\"fire\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; breath."}
