{"id": "26637", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26637", "title": "Hell Rift", "text": "Hell Rifts were gateways from the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Burning Hells&lt;/a&gt; into the &lt;a href=\"High%20Heavens\"&gt;High Heavens&lt;/a&gt;, utilized by &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt; during his assault on the &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt;s' realm. They were maintained by Diablo's &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;, which, if removed, would lead to the Hell Rift collapsing.\nThe Rifts were sealed by &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nHell Rifts are two small dungeons that can be found in &lt;a href=\"Act%20IV%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act IV&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn &lt;a href=\"Campaign%20Mode\"&gt;Campaign Mode&lt;/a&gt;, there are two separate Hell Rifts, each with a single level, with entrance portals in &lt;a href=\"Gardens%20of%20Hope\"&gt;Gardens of Hope&lt;/a&gt; 1st and 2nd Tier. Demonic Corruption must be destroyed to find the portals. Inside the rifts are Rift Oculi, which sustain the portals leading to &lt;a href=\"High%20Heavens\"&gt;High Heavens&lt;/a&gt;. Through the Rifts, &lt;a href=\"demons\"&gt;demons&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Realm of Terror&lt;/a&gt; send reinforcements to assault the Gardens of Hope. Each Hell Rift is guaranteed to have a &lt;a href=\"Super%20Unique\"&gt;Super Unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Mallet%20Lord\"&gt;Mallet Lord&lt;/a&gt; guarding it, either &lt;a href=\"Hammermash\"&gt;Hammermash&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Sledge\"&gt;Sledge&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Adventure%20Mode\"&gt;Adventure Mode&lt;/a&gt;, the Hell Rift is a single two-level dungeon which is only accessible by &lt;a href=\"Waypoint\"&gt;Waypoint&lt;/a&gt;. There is no portal from the Gardens, although the dungeon exit obelisk leads to the Gardens 1st Tier next to a Corrupt Growth, matching the Hell Portal location in the campaign. There are no Rift Oculi. The Mallet Lords only appear on Level 2, and are fairly rare spawns unless there is a &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; for one of them; it is possible albeit rare for both to be present on the same level.\nHell Rifts may appear as a layout for &lt;a href=\"Nephalem%20Rift\"&gt;Nephalem Rift&lt;/a&gt;s.\nThese dungeons are very dangerous for Hardcore characters, because combat often starts \"immediately\"\u00a0after you enter the red portal. In other words, demons will have a chance to attack the player before the level is even fully loaded."}
