{"id": "53198", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53198", "title": "Hellbreeder Nest", "text": "Hellbreeder Nest is an &lt;a href=\"event%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;event&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Act%20IV%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act IV&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\". It takes place in the &lt;a href=\"Blessed%20Chancel\"&gt;Blessed Chancel&lt;/a&gt;, a \"dungeon\" connected to &lt;a href=\"Gardens%20of%20Hope\"&gt;Gardens of Hope&lt;/a&gt; 3rd Tier, where a &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; may be offered to complete it.\nUpon arrival at the main square area of the Chancel, a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Morlu%20Caster\"&gt;Morlu Caster&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"Zao%27Kapazao\"&gt;Zao'Kapazao&lt;/a&gt; stands on the near side. He will summon a couple &lt;a href=\"Corrupt%20Hellbreeder\"&gt;Corrupt Hellbreeder&lt;/a&gt; nests when approached. For each 25-33% health he loses, he shields himself with a green force field and becomes invulnerable, then teleports away to another spot around the square, leaving another Corrupt Hellbreeder behind. When he is pursued, he summons three more nests surrounding himself, then becomes vulnerable again. This process repeats until he is dead, ending the event.\nThe Hellbreeders, which spawn &lt;a href=\"Vilebat\"&gt;Vilebat&lt;/a&gt;s periodically, also pop up along the sides of the square when walking around it. None of the nests need to be killed to complete the event."}
