{"id": "27712", "revid": "34609461", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27712", "title": "Hellfire Amulet", "text": "The Hellfire Amulet is a &lt;a href=\"Craftable%20items\"&gt;craftable&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"amulets\"&gt;amulet&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It rolls stats for level 70, but only requires &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 1 to be equipped.\nThe Hellfire Amulet essentially gives the character five passive skills: it will have a secondary legendary affix that provides a randomized passive skill of the class who crafted it. The passive skill cannot be re-rolled once an amulet is crafted, so it may be very challenging to get an optimal combination of the skill and stats. Each passive skill only works for the class that normally has it: one cannot use this amulet to gain a passive skill of another class. Passives also do not duplicate if taken normally and on the amulet.\nSince it automatically\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Bind%20on%20Account\"&gt;binds to the player's account&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0upon being made and requires materials only obtainable at level 70, it is unobtainable without access to\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Reaper%20of%20Souls\"&gt;Reaper of Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nThis is one of the few Legendary items in game that cannot be extracted into &lt;a href=\"Kanai%27s%20Cube\"&gt;Kanai's Cube&lt;/a&gt;. As of patch 2.3.0, it always rolls a guaranteed &lt;a href=\"socket\"&gt;socket&lt;/a&gt;.\nCrafting.\nIt can be acquired through the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Infernal%20Machine\"&gt;Infernal Machine&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0event. The crafting plan can be acquired from &lt;a href=\"Squirt%20the%20Peddler\"&gt;Squirt the Peddler&lt;/a&gt; in for 100,000 gold.\nTo make a Hellfire Amulet, one will need all the same materials as those for the level 70\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Hellfire%20Ring%20%28other%29\"&gt;Hellfire Ring&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0(10,000 gold, &lt;a href=\"Heart%20of%20Evil\"&gt;Heart of Evil&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Vial%20of%20Putridness\"&gt;Vial of Putridness&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Idol%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Idol of Terror&lt;/a&gt;).\nThe amulet can be crafted in three variants: of &lt;a href=\"Dexterity\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;, of &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; and of &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, like the old Hellfire Rings. There is no option to craft amulets with &lt;a href=\"Vitality\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt;.\nRegardless of whether the player chooses their current class's core stat, the passive rolled is guaranteed to be for their class. \nUnlike all other &lt;a href=\"Jewelry\"&gt;Jewelry&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Enchanting\"&gt;Enchanting&lt;/a&gt; the Hellfire Amulet doesn't require any &lt;a href=\"gems\"&gt;gems&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "45184", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45184", "title": "Hellfire Augur", "text": "s are a type of &lt;a href=\"Khazra%20Shaman\"&gt;Khazra Shaman&lt;/a&gt; that have sworn allegiance to the forces of the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Burning Hells&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nThough the &lt;a href=\"khazra\"&gt;khazra&lt;/a&gt; are no strangers to abhorrent acts, some clans find serving &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt; controversial. Augurs coax their reluctant kin into &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;ic subjugation, and are rewarded with command of &lt;a href=\"fire\"&gt;flames&lt;/a&gt; and the ability to read prophecy in the &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;-ash of those they kill.\nIn-game.\ns appear as &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;Realm of Damnation&lt;/a&gt;, specifically in the &lt;a href=\"Citadel%20of%20the%20Damned\"&gt;Citadel of the Damned&lt;/a&gt;. They attack by igniting their staffs and hurling them at an enemy. Similar to a boomerang, the staff returns to its owner."}
