{"id": "41150", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41150", "title": "Helliquary", "text": "Helliquary is a gameplay system of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is intended for endgame play.\nLore.\nThe Helliquary is an ornate chest fashioned from precious metals, crystal, and gems. It was built to locate particularly destructive &lt;a href=\"Demon\"&gt;demons&lt;/a&gt; and trap their &lt;a href=\"essence\"&gt;essence&lt;/a&gt; when they're slain. Once the demon is defeated, the Helliquary can turn their remains into power an &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt; can take advantage of. Though unstable, the Helliquary is capable of funneling the power of defeated demons to a sufficiently daring subject. The remains of the demon are sealed inside the Helliquary, containing the darkness, and the energy is channeled into the subject, without any noticeable corruption. However, the risks of this process remain unknown.\nAt least in theory, the Helliquary is capable of channeling the essence of &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;s as well.\nThe Helliquary was designed to be reinforced by &lt;a href=\"scoria\"&gt;scoria&lt;/a&gt;. The stronger it becomes, the stronger its user(s) become as well. The device is small enough and light enough to be lifted by an ordinary &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;.\nSince it was upgraded by Rayek, multiple parts of a demon can be sealed in the Helliquary at a time.\nHistory.\nThe Helliquary was built by &lt;a href=\"Rayek\"&gt;Rayek&lt;/a&gt; with the aid of &lt;a href=\"Charsi\"&gt;Charsi&lt;/a&gt;. Rayek hoped to use his creation to stop demonic incursions before they happened, and prevent the doom that came to his &lt;a href=\"Northern%20Steppes\"&gt;homeland&lt;/a&gt; from ruining other lands. After building the device, he detected dark energy coming from the &lt;a href=\"Einfrinn%20Tree\"&gt;Einfrinn Tree&lt;/a&gt;. Studying the tree, he discovered that the Helliquary had become entangled with energy leaking from the tree, and that the tree itself was holding back a powerful demon. He suggested using the Helliquary to lend power to the tree, as it was growing weaker by the minute.\nTo this end, he enlisted the aid of a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;hero/group of heroes&lt;/a&gt;. After receiving a vision of the future from the tree, they retrieved the remains of &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Herald%20Pyl\"&gt;Chaos Herald Pyl&lt;/a&gt;, which were used by the device.\n&lt;a href=\"Timeline%231272\"&gt;Two years later&lt;/a&gt;, Rayek was put in charge of &lt;a href=\"Cain%27s%20Workshop\"&gt;Cain's Workshop&lt;/a&gt; after Cain travelled. He built an alter in the backroom of the workshop that could boost the sensing range of the Helliquary. Unfortunately, an energy reading originating from &lt;a href=\"Bilefen\"&gt;Bilefen&lt;/a&gt; interfered with the altar. Rayek sent a letter to &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; to help him track the source of the energy. The interference originated from a &lt;a href=\"cracks\"&gt;fissure&lt;/a&gt; venting demonic energy which corrupted the surrounding &lt;a href=\"animal\"&gt;wildlife&lt;/a&gt;. Using the energy as a reference, Rayek located similar fissures at &lt;a href=\"Ashwold%20Cemetery\"&gt;Ashwold Cemetery&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wood\"&gt;Dark Wood&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Tundra\"&gt;Frozen Tundra&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Shassar%20Sea\"&gt;Shassar Sea&lt;/a&gt;. Rayek asked the Shard-seeker to gather energy samples from the other fissures, but not before upgrading the Helliquary. By placing the improved Helliquary on the altar, and using the procured energy samples as a reference, Rayek scried a new set of demons \u2014 the third so far. He named them the \"&lt;a href=\"Hearthrot\"&gt;Hearthrot&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGameplay.\nThe Helliquary becomes available once the player's character reaches &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;level&lt;/a&gt; 36. After this, players will reunite with &lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;Deckard Cain&lt;/a&gt; in his &lt;a href=\"Cain%27s%20Workshop\"&gt;workshop&lt;/a&gt;. Cain introduces the player to &lt;a href=\"Rayek\"&gt;Rayek&lt;/a&gt;, who's developed the Helliquary. This is part of the &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"Opening%20the%20Helliquary\"&gt;Opening the Helliquary&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nOverview.\nThe Helliquary is a powerful creation forged to defend against battle some of the most powerful demons from the Burning Hells.\nDemonic Remains.\n\"Main article: &lt;a href=\"Demonic%20Remains\"&gt;Demonic Remains&lt;/a&gt;\"\nOther Information.\nPlayers may solo the Helliquary, or do so as part of a group. The Helliquary allows up to 8 players at a time (this can be in a &lt;a href=\"warband\"&gt;warband&lt;/a&gt;) to locate and defeat &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt;es in order to not only power up their characters, but also to benchmark their power. If a player's character defeats a boss, they receive a power boost. Multiple difficulty levels are available for each boss; the difficulty of bosses increases with each subsequent &lt;a href=\"Hell%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt; difficulty. Some Hell difficulties can only be unlocked through defeating corresponding Helliquary bosses. Within the Helliquary &lt;a href=\"dungeon%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;dungeon&lt;/a&gt; itself, the difficulty scales to players' respective difficulties.\nEach player has one revive in the Helliquary. Otherwise, they need to rely on other players to revive them. When a player dies more than once during a raid, resurrecting them will incur an increasing cooldown.\nThe Helliquary has a leaderboard system, where warbands compete for the best positions. The top leaderboard team gains extra scoria. For a warband to take part in a Helliquary raid, at least four warband players must be present. The other four slots can be filled by other players. Completing the raid this way will still yield extra warband rewards for the warband members.\nSuccessfully completing a warband Helliquary raid for the first time will grant warband members an additional 400% drop rate increase for Sealed Warband Chests. This bonus resets every Monday and Thursday.\nObjectives are cycled weekly.\nIn a full (8-member) raid, the top 3 damage contributors earn a Chest of Glory containing 6 &lt;a href=\"Beguiling%20Dust\"&gt;Beguiling Dust&lt;/a&gt;. This chest opens automatically.\nList of Bosses.\nWrathborne.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Wrathborne\"&gt;Wrathborne&lt;/a&gt; are the first set of Helliquary bosses. Their order of introduction is as follows:\nVoidwound.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Voidwound\"&gt;Voidwound&lt;/a&gt; are the second set of Helliquary bosses. They were all introduced to \"Immortal\" simultaniously as part of the &lt;a href=\"Terror%27s%20Tide\"&gt;Terror's Tide&lt;/a&gt; update. Their order of progression is as follows:\nHearthrot.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Hearthrot\"&gt;Hearthrot&lt;/a&gt; are the third set of Helliquary bosses, released as part of the &lt;a href=\"Destruction%27s%20Wake\"&gt;Destruction's Wake&lt;/a&gt; update. Their order of progression are as follows:\nSoulhewn.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Soulhewn\"&gt;Soulhewn&lt;/a&gt; are the fourth set of Helliquary bosses, released as part of the &lt;a href=\"Splintered%20Souls\"&gt;Splintered Souls&lt;/a&gt; update. Their order of progression are as follows:\nStormspawn.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Stormspawn\"&gt;Stormspawn&lt;/a&gt; are the fifth set of Helliquary bosses, released as part of the &lt;a href=\"Age%20of%20Unmaking\"&gt;Age of Unmaking&lt;/a&gt; update. Their order of progression are as follows:\nDreadbirth.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Dreadbirth\"&gt;Dreadbirth&lt;/a&gt; are the sixth set of Helliquary bosses, released as part of the &lt;a href=\"Shattered%20Sanctuary\"&gt;Shattered Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; update. Their order of progression are as follows:\nDemons by Difficulty.\nEach &lt;a href=\"Difficulty\"&gt;Difficulty&lt;/a&gt; offers a different set of demons to challenge. The last boss on each difficulty must be defeated to unlock the next difficulty, with the exception of Hell I, which is unlocked by defeating Lassal.\nHistory.\nThe Helliquary originally unlocked between levels 41\u201345. Originally, the Helliquary was said to have been developed by &lt;a href=\"Charsi\"&gt;Charsi&lt;/a&gt;, while in the final version, its creation can better be attributed to Rayek.\nAt some point, the Helliquary became available when the player completed the &lt;a href=\"Bilefen\"&gt;Bilefen&lt;/a&gt; questline. In the final version, the player just needs to reach level 36.\nOriginally, the Helliquary could only be attemtped as part of a group. As of the &lt;a href=\"Terror%27s%20Tide\"&gt;Terror's Tide&lt;/a&gt; update, the Helliquary may be soloed.\nThe original Helliquary dropped &lt;a href=\"Scoria\"&gt;Scoria&lt;/a&gt;, which had to be taken to &lt;a href=\"Charsi\"&gt;Charsi&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt; to be refined into &lt;a href=\"Hellfire%20Scoria\"&gt;Hellfire Scoria&lt;/a&gt;; this was removed when the Voidwound bosses were added.\nOriginally 4 members of the same Warband had to participate in a Helliquary raid to earn Warband Points. This requirement was dropped in the September 21 2023 update.\nIn the &lt;a href=\"Unending%20Storm\"&gt;Unending Storm&lt;/a&gt; update, the &lt;a href=\"Difficulty\"&gt;difficulties&lt;/a&gt; were reworked, and as a result the bosses available to challenge were updated as well. The bosses for each difficulty before the update were as follows:\nBecause there was no room for them in the new system, Vitaath, Gorgothra, Izilech, the Twin Terrors and Vhansoon can no longer be challenged. Their &lt;a href=\"Trophies%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;trophies&lt;/a&gt; were retired and moved into the Legacy category. Nevertheless, these bosses (except for the Twin Terrors, which didn't appear before) can still appear as echoes during a Helliquary Surge.\nIn the update, the quick matching feature was extended to work cross-server.\nOriginally the Heavy Austere Chests had to be opened by having four players activate the chest at the same time. In the update, this was changed such that the chests open automatically.\nIn the update, Vitaath, Gorgothra, Izilech, and the Twin Terrors were added back on Normal difficulty.\nOriginally the Chest of Glory for top damage contributors had to be opened manually. This was changed in the update to open automatically.\nThe update added a damage tracker showing the top 4 players, and a spectator mode for dead players to continue to watch the raid."}
{"id": "46270", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46270", "title": "Helliquary Gauntlet", "text": "Helliquary Gauntlet is a game mode in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", unlocked after a player defeats &lt;a href=\"Catarag\"&gt;Catarag&lt;/a&gt;. Here, players battle the &lt;a href=\"Helliquary\"&gt;Helliquary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt;es in succession.\nPlayers can begin a Helliquary Gauntlet raid as frequently as they like and will receive loot such as random &lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;Set Items&lt;/a&gt;, random &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary Items&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Demonic%20Remains\"&gt;Demonic Remains&lt;/a&gt; and more for their first completion. Players who land a top-10 spot on the Leaderboard for their server by the end of the week will receive the Voidwound Gauntlet Champion Avatar Frame to sport during the Helliquary Gauntlet season. If that player can retain their top-10 spot until the season ends, they\u2019ll get to keep their Avatar Frame for good.\nThe set of bosses rotates when major updates with new Helliquary bosses are released."}
{"id": "51576", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51576", "title": "Helliquary Surge", "text": " is a game mode in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It has a chance to occur immediately after defeating a &lt;a href=\"Helliquary\"&gt;Helliquary&lt;/a&gt; boss. When it occurs, instead of the exit portal, a rift appears, which the raid members must activate. The rift activates when either all players interact with it, or 20 seconds after the first player interacts with it. Once activated, a sequence of three Echoes must be defeated, which are Helliquary bosses at reduced strength. A chest containing gold, equipment and &lt;a href=\"Beguiling%20Dust\"&gt;Beguiling Dust&lt;/a&gt; appears if the bosses are defeated within the time limit.\nEchoes of retired bosses such as &lt;a href=\"Gorgothra%20the%20Claimer\"&gt;Gorgothra the Claimer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Vhansoon%2C%20Desolation%27s%20Scourge\"&gt;Vhansoon, Desolation's Scourge&lt;/a&gt; can still appear during a Helliquary Surge."}
{"id": "44085", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44085", "title": "Hellish Hunt", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;Realm of Damnation&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\n\"There are few &lt;a href=\"beast\"&gt;beast&lt;/a&gt;s more dangerous than &lt;a href=\"drub\"&gt;drub&lt;/a&gt;s on a hunt. They are ambush predators capable of taking down prey four times their size. I want to see your worth, &lt;a href=\"Adventurer\"&gt;Adventurer&lt;/a&gt;. Draw out these beasts from where they hide and kill them.\""}
{"id": "16866", "revid": "867479", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16866", "title": "Hellish Projectile", "text": "Hellish Projectile (also known as Skull Missile) is a lethal &lt;a href=\"Monster%20Skill\"&gt;Monster Skill&lt;/a&gt; and the signature move of &lt;a href=\"Mephisto\"&gt;Mephisto&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Act%20Boss\"&gt;Act Boss&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"The%20Infernal%20Gate\"&gt;Act III&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nHellish Projectile looks like a white, blazing orb and is fired in a straight line. An 'incoming missile' sound can be heard as well.\nHellish Projectile can be very dangerous as it deals horrible damage, usually killing &lt;a href=\"Hirelings\"&gt;Hirelings&lt;/a&gt; and minions in a single hit. Players can expect to relinquish at least a third of their health. Mephisto only uses Skull Missile when at range, so closing in on him should remove the danger."}
{"id": "19386", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19386", "title": "Hellish Staff of Herding", "text": "The Hellish Staff of Herding was a &lt;a href=\"Craftable%20items\"&gt;craftable&lt;/a&gt; staff in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It was needed to access &lt;a href=\"Whimsyshire\"&gt;Whimsyshire&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Hell%20%28Difficulty%29\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt; difficulty. As of version 2.0, any version of the &lt;a href=\"Staff%20of%20Herding\"&gt;Staff of Herding&lt;/a&gt; will grant the player access to Whimsyshire on any difficulty, so it is no longer necessary nor possible to upgrade the staff.\nIt has an &lt;a href=\"Item%20Level\"&gt;Item Level&lt;/a&gt; of 1, and requires character level 1 to be used.\nStats.\nHellish Staff of HerdingStaff\nCrafting.\nThe Hellish Staff of Herding could be crafted using the Plan: Hellish Staff of Herding, 500,000 gold (20,000 on console), and the &lt;a href=\"Nightmarish%20Staff%20of%20Herding\"&gt;Nightmarish Staff of Herding&lt;/a&gt;. Upgraded versions of the plans could be bought from &lt;a href=\"Gorell%20the%20Quartermaster\"&gt;Gorell the Quartermaster&lt;/a&gt; beside the Armory in &lt;a href=\"Bastion%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Bastion's Keep&lt;/a&gt; Stronghold. Once again, it could be bought \"only\" in the Prime Evil quest, just like its predecessor"}
