{"id": "6775", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6775", "title": "Hellslayer (Diablo II)", "text": "Hellslayer is an &lt;a href=\"Elite%20Items\"&gt;elite&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; , a type of &lt;a href=\"Axes\"&gt;axe&lt;/a&gt; from \"\".\nA robust weapon that gives high bonuses to both &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Life\"&gt;Life&lt;/a&gt;, Hellslayer also dishes out an extremely high maximum damage; it in fact has the highest potential maximum damage out of any unique axe. Still, a player has to be at high enough character level to have this bonus.\nHellslayer is cousin to another unique axe, . While the Reaver has a higher minimum damage, Hellslayer has a higher potential maximum damage and added &lt;a href=\"Fire\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage.\nStats.\nTwo-Hand Damage: \nRequired Level: 66\nRequired Strength: 189\nRequired Dexterity: 33\nDurability: 40\nAxe Class \u2013 Normal Attack Speed"}
{"id": "50911", "revid": "52469887", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50911", "title": "Hellslayer Bounties", "text": "Hellslayer Bounties are a type of &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", added in the &lt;a href=\"Precipice%20of%20Horror\"&gt;Precipice of Horror&lt;/a&gt; update.\nGameplay.\nHellslayer Bounties can be done either solo or as part of a group. To access them, the player(s) must be at I difficulty or higher. Players can combine 4 normal, active bounties into a Hellslayer Bounty at the bounty board in &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt; for the cost of one &lt;a href=\"Terror%20Essence\"&gt;Terror Essence&lt;/a&gt;. Once done, the player(s) must travel to the zone listed on the bounty, locate the Hellslayer Bounties portal, and engage in a more forgiving style of &lt;a href=\"Oblivion%20Pillar\"&gt;Oblivion Pillar&lt;/a&gt; gameplay."}
