{"id": "44092", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44092", "title": "Helltide", "text": "Helltides are a gameplay feature of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nHelltides are &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;ic events that affect &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Reign%20of%20Enmity\"&gt;Reign of Enmity&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Demon\"&gt;Demon&lt;/a&gt;s of &lt;a href=\"Lilith\"&gt;Lilith&lt;/a&gt; are empowered, her mightiest minions out in greater force. The very ground of the mortal realm is morphed by the surge in demonic activity as the sky darkens, rivers run red, and meteors fall upon the mortal realm, as Sanctuary gives way to &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Hell's&lt;/a&gt; influence. Entire &lt;a href=\"town\"&gt;town&lt;/a&gt;s can be caught in helltides, their inhabitants entranced into worshipping Hell.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Wolves\"&gt;Iron Wolves&lt;/a&gt; sought to rally forces against the demons who emerged in helltides, and salvaged demonic &lt;a href=\"corpse\"&gt;corpse&lt;/a&gt;s left in a helltide's wake. After the &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Harvest\"&gt;Blood Harvest&lt;/a&gt;, the legions of Hell regrouped to coordinate a display of force, resulting in a new form of Helltide.\nIt was later discovered that these new Helltides were a harbinger of things to come, as the legions of Hell mustered behind its &lt;a href=\"Gates%20of%20Hell\"&gt;gates&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nHelltides are region-wide events that are available to players from World Tier I onwards. Overall monster density shifts with tier. &lt;a href=\"Town\"&gt;Town&lt;/a&gt;s can be temporarily consumed by a helltide, forcing their NPCs into worship.\nHelltides occur randomly in the open world, and last for about an hour. Helltides appear on the map as red zones. A Helltide lasts 55 minutes, with 5 minutes of downtime before the next one appears in a different area.\nDemons in an area are empowered, and their monster level is greater than the player level, but their loot drops correspond to the surge in difficulty. &lt;a href=\"Monster\"&gt;Monster&lt;/a&gt;s killed in a Helltide potentially drop &lt;a href=\"cinder\"&gt;cinder&lt;/a&gt;s that can be spent to open Helltide Chests in the respective region. Some Helltide chests can drop &lt;a href=\"unique%20items\"&gt;unique items&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Hellworm\"&gt;Hellworm&lt;/a&gt;s will sometimes rise from the ground, depositing more demons.\nSome crafting materials are only found in Helltides, such as the &lt;a href=\"Fiend%20Rose\"&gt;Fiend Rose&lt;/a&gt;.\nHellspires can be found within a helltide. When activated, the spire generates a wave of demons for the player to fight. Ravenous Soulspires drain a player's health.\nAs a player cleaves their way through a Helltide, they generate Threat. Threat is earned based on the difficulty of the monsters the player slays and how often they're opening Tortured Gifts within a Helltide. There are three Threat Levels in total, with each level increasing the danger and frequency of ambushes. Once a player hits Level 3, they will become Hell-Marked. When a player has been Hell-Marked, they'll be besieged by a frenzy of densely packed monsters. If they make it out alive, a &lt;a href=\"Hellborn\"&gt;Hellborn&lt;/a&gt; will come for them. The Threat level resets once the Hellborn ambush has been activated, or if the player is killed.\nDevelopment.\nHelltides were originally only available at World Tier Three."}
