{"id": "27709", "revid": "43723075", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27709", "title": "Helltooth Harness", "text": "Helltooth Harness\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Witch%20Doctor\"&gt;Witch Doctor&lt;/a&gt; class\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;item set&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIt is the defensive class set for\u00a0Witch Doctors\u00a0for level 70. This set can only drop at\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Torment%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Torment&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0difficulty.\nThe set was created by &lt;a href=\"Jeram\"&gt;Jeram&lt;/a&gt; of the Whispering Valley from &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; bones.\nAll of the items in this set are restricted to Witch Doctors.\u00a0Even\u00a0&lt;a href=\"transmogrification\"&gt;transmogrification&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0of these items is only available to Witch Doctors.\nPieces.\nThe set consists of six pieces. All six are required to complete the set, and all six are Witch Doctor-restricted.\nSet Bonus:\nThe first bonus &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20damage\"&gt;Elemental damage&lt;/a&gt; type matches the one that Witch Doctor has highest skill bonus for.\nSecond and third bonuses are multiplicative to other similar modifiers. They do not stack from multiple casts, instead being refreshed. Damage bonus applies to the skills themselves, not necessarily against foes hit by Wall of Death.\nDevelopment.\nPrior to patch 2.3, set bonuses of this set were different.\nThe last bonus stacked, if multiple Walls of Zombies were summoned to cover the same area with acid."}
