{"id": "33679", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33679", "title": "Henknoc Tribe", "text": "The Henknoc Tribe is/was a tribe.\nHistory.\nThe Henknoc existed as far back as the days of the original Barbarian kingdom (long before the coming of &lt;a href=\"Rakkis\"&gt;Rakkis&lt;/a&gt;), and resided in the jungles found on the southern end of the kingdom. At some point during this period, the Henknoc were in conflict with another tribe. However, when &lt;a href=\"Korlic\"&gt;Korlic&lt;/a&gt;, leader of the Henknoc, rescued the son of the enemy tribe's chieftain, the conflict between the two tribes abated. Korlic was later summoned to guard the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt;, and the boy he saved took his place as tribal chief."}
{"id": "31838", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31838", "title": "Henri", "text": "Henri was the pet cat of &lt;a href=\"Paul\"&gt;Paul&lt;/a&gt;, a craftsman. As his master worked to create a &lt;a href=\"Henri%27s%20Perquisition\"&gt;mojo&lt;/a&gt;, Henri, in pursuit of a mouse, leapt into the mix, becoming part of the mojo itself. Henri is said to be eternally searching for that mouse, which has never been seen since."}
{"id": "31832", "revid": "25771421", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31832", "title": "Henri's Perquisition", "text": "Henri's Perquisition is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"mojos\"&gt;mojo&lt;/a&gt; for the &lt;a href=\"Witch%20Doctor\"&gt;Witch Doctor&lt;/a&gt; that was introduced in &lt;a href=\"Season%204\"&gt;Season 4&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 70 to drop.\nThis item originally only dropped during &lt;a href=\"Season\"&gt;Season&lt;/a&gt; Four, but since its end, drops for all characters.\nThe unique affix works the first time after combat starts, separately for each enemy. Leaving combat and engaging the unfinished foe again will them anew. It affects all sources of damage, including affixes and on-death explosions. In return, it only applies to attacks that hit the Witch Doctor: damage done to &lt;a href=\"pets\"&gt;pets&lt;/a&gt; will not be reduced and will not trigger Charm."}
{"id": "51296", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51296", "title": "Henriet", "text": "Henriet was a &lt;a href=\"crusader\"&gt;crusader&lt;/a&gt; who never took an apprentice. After he died, his name was crossed from the &lt;a href=\"Crusaders\"&gt;crusader&lt;/a&gt; scrolls. Though &lt;a href=\"Bygone%20Eidolon\"&gt;his pants&lt;/a&gt; is all that remain of him, his deeds still persist in memory and steel.\nIn-game.\nHenriet is referenced in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", in the &lt;a href=\"Legendary\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"pants\"&gt;pants&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"Bygone%20Eidolon\"&gt;Bygone Eidolon&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "4496", "revid": "839260", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4496", "title": "Hephasto", "text": ""}
{"id": "2489", "revid": "126761", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2489", "title": "Hephasto The Armorer", "text": ""}
{"id": "2453", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2453", "title": "Hephasto the Armorer", "text": "Hephasto the Armorer was the head armorer of the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Burning Hells&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nHephasto was one of the weapon smiths of &lt;a href=\"Inarius\"&gt;Inarius&lt;/a&gt; that was corrupted by &lt;a href=\"Mephisto\"&gt;Mephisto&lt;/a&gt; as punishment for the destruction of his &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20the%20Triune\"&gt;temple&lt;/a&gt;. He rose through the ranks of Hell to become a master armorer for the forces of darkness, serving as a minion of &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal&lt;/a&gt;. He toiled away in the &lt;a href=\"Hellforge\"&gt;Hellforge&lt;/a&gt;, molding incredible weapons for his comrades to use in battle. He would twist &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s to use as catalysts in the forge, and the remaining coals carried the mark of their torment. While his place at the fires of the Hellforge was coveted amongst jealous &lt;a href=\"Overlord\"&gt;Overlord&lt;/a&gt;s, none dared cross &lt;a href=\"sword\"&gt;sword&lt;/a&gt;s with him lest he take the anguish of his lost glory out upon their bloated bodies.\nOne of Hephasto's creations was the &lt;a href=\"Shard%20of%20Hate\"&gt;Shard of Hate&lt;/a&gt;, which he delivered to Mephisto personally. \nHephasto was struck down by a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20II\"&gt;group of heroes&lt;/a&gt; which had followed &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt; into Hell during the &lt;a href=\"Prime%20Evil\"&gt;Prime Evil&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231264\"&gt;return&lt;/a&gt;. Taking his &lt;a href=\"Hellforge%20Hammer\"&gt;hammer&lt;/a&gt;, they were able to shatter the &lt;a href=\"soulstone\"&gt;soulstone&lt;/a&gt; that contained Mephisto, and later, do the same to Diablo. Years later, &lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;Deckard Cain&lt;/a&gt; reflected that it was possible that Hephasto could return, given that according to ancient &lt;a href=\"Vizjerei\"&gt;Vizjerei&lt;/a&gt; texts, demons have the potential to be reborn in Hell after their death.\nIn-game.\nDiablo II.\nHephasto is found in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\", located in the &lt;a href=\"River%20of%20Flame\"&gt;River of Flame&lt;/a&gt; zone. He is identical in appearance to &lt;a href=\"the%20Smith\"&gt;the Smith&lt;/a&gt; which can be found earlier in the &lt;a href=\"barracks\"&gt;barracks&lt;/a&gt;, but is tougher and stronger than his subordinate, and with green skin. Upon defeat, he drops the &lt;a href=\"Hellforge%20Hammer\"&gt;Hellforge Hammer&lt;/a&gt;, which is required to destroy &lt;a href=\"Mephisto\"&gt;Mephisto&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Soulstone\"&gt;Soulstone&lt;/a&gt;.\nSpecial Abilities:\nHephasto's spawns with an random aura and is an extremely difficult enemy to face, especially if players are fighting him around &lt;a href=\"Abyss%20Knights\"&gt;Abyss Knights&lt;/a&gt;, particularly in Hell difficulty when there is a substantial reduction in resistances. He is weakest against &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; so use poison attacks against him whenever possible.\nDiablo III.\nHephasto is mentioned in flavor text for the &lt;a href=\"Shard%20of%20Hate\"&gt;Shard of Hate&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hellforge%20Ember\"&gt;Hellforge Ember&lt;/a&gt;.\nPersonality and Traits.\nHephasto was a hulking demon and moved slowly. As a minion of Baal, was driven to destroy everything he touched. Yet at the same time, he possessed the ability to create. Cain speculated that Hephasto managed to channel his destructive nature into the armaments he forged. It is said that Hephasto took great pride in the knowledge that his creations would cause untold death and carnage. It is also said that the armaments he forged could only be used in acts of destruction and desecration.\nHephasto had wide arms and powerful arms, built up by the thousands of strikes with his &lt;a href=\"Hellforge%20Hammer\"&gt;Hellforge Hammer&lt;/a&gt; against the &lt;a href=\"Anvil%20of%20Fury\"&gt;Anvil of Fury&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4497", "revid": "839260", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4497", "title": "Hephasto the Armourer", "text": ""}
{"id": "19740", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19740", "title": "Herald of Pestilence", "text": "Heralds of Pestilence are roughly humanoid &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s. They are known for their asymmetrical arms, one of which is long and tentacle-like and capable of burrowing underground to attack foes.\nIn-game.\nDiablo Immortal.\nHeralds of Pestilence appear in the &lt;a href=\"Domain%20of%20Horror\"&gt;Domain of Horror&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDiablo III.\nHeralds of Pestilence are found in the second half of\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Act%20III%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act III&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nHeralds move and attack rather slowly, but have two modes in which to attack.\nFrom afar, they are plunging their oversized arm into the ground, emerging it near the player some time later. Once emerged, the arm starts pumping toxins, dealing Poison damage to everything within roughly 10 yards like a Plagued pool. This attack lasts at least 3 seconds, and Herald cannot do anything else while channeling it. Use it to your advantage to attack the Herald while he is helpless. Being &lt;a href=\"Knockback\"&gt;Knockback&lt;/a&gt;ed or disabled with the hand in the ground will cause a Herald to stop channeling the attack.\nIn melee, they just deliver a close combat hit, also dealing a lot of Poison damage and inflicting\u00a0&lt;a href=\"poison\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt;.\nOverall, they are more of supporting fighters, as their ranged attack is easily avoidable, but multiple Heralds can infest a large area, blocking much of the path."}
