{"id": "43054", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43054", "title": "Hero's Journey", "text": "Hero's Journey is a reward system in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". \nThe mode unlocks after completing \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Realm%20of%20the%20Dead\"&gt;The Realm of the Dead&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Tundra\"&gt;Frozen Tundra&lt;/a&gt; zone. Hero\u2019s Journey assigns players various objectives that scale in difficulty as their &lt;a href=\"Paragon\"&gt;Paragon&lt;/a&gt; level increases. Upon completing each chapter, players can win a variety of rewards. These range from large sums of &lt;a href=\"gold\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"platinum\"&gt;platinum&lt;/a&gt;, to &lt;a href=\"Aspirant%27s%20Keys\"&gt;Aspirant's Keys&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Crest\"&gt;Legendary Crest&lt;/a&gt;s, and a special Portrait Frame or Portal cosmetic.\nHero's Journey is a &lt;a href=\"Season%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;seasonal&lt;/a&gt; event, with seasons lasting multiple months. After the end of the season, new goals for chapters 1 through 4 are unlocked, with chapters 5 and 6 added in later updates."}
