{"id": "26793", "revid": "25771421", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26793", "title": "Hexing Pants of Mr. Yan", "text": "Hexing Pants of Mr. Yan\u00a0are &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"pants\"&gt;pants&lt;/a&gt; in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". They require\u00a0&lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt;\u00a031 to drop.\nThe special affix is useful for some melee builds that rely on movement (&lt;a href=\"Whirlwind%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Whirlwind&lt;/a&gt; s or &lt;a href=\"Explosive%20Blast\"&gt;Explosive Blast&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Wizard\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt;s), but traditional builds will have little use for it, as most skills may not be used on the move. One might also want to have a healthy stacking of &lt;a href=\"Crowd%20Control\"&gt;Crowd Control&lt;/a&gt; status effect reduction stat on other items, to minimize the amount of time spent &lt;a href=\"Immobilized\"&gt;Immobilized&lt;/a&gt;. These pants are most effective with &lt;a href=\"pet\"&gt;pet&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"damage%20over%20time\"&gt;damage over time&lt;/a&gt; builds. Any source of movement will count, including charging skills (like &lt;a href=\"Dashing%20Strike\"&gt;Dashing Strike&lt;/a&gt;), and even flying away from &lt;a href=\"Knockback\"&gt;Knockback&lt;/a&gt;.\nAll four effects (buffs / debuffs to damage and resource generation) are multiplicative to other similar modifiers. However, it \"does\" show up on the character screen.\nFor channeled skills that force movement, coupling this item with &lt;a href=\"Mantle%20of%20Channeling\"&gt;Mantle of Channeling&lt;/a&gt; may yield positive results."}
