{"id": "36917", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36917", "title": "High Council", "text": ""}
{"id": "4313", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4313", "title": "High Council of Zakarum", "text": "The High Council of Zakarum was a body within the &lt;a href=\"Zakarum\"&gt;Zakarum&lt;/a&gt; faith.\nLore.\nThe High Council originally served as the leaders of the Zakarum faith, though were apparently still beneath the &lt;a href=\"Que-Hegan\"&gt;Que-Hegan&lt;/a&gt; in authority. \nHistory.\nThe High Council was formed after the &lt;a href=\"Horadrim\"&gt;Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; delivered the &lt;a href=\"soulstone\"&gt;soulstone&lt;/a&gt; containing &lt;a href=\"Mephisto\"&gt;Mephisto&lt;/a&gt;'s essence to the Zakarum. The High Council was charged with overseeing Mephisto's containment. Over time however, Mephisto was able to corrupt the Council from within. This process took generations, and each generation of the High Council was more under Mephisto's sway than the one preceeding it. \nThe Council reached its nadir in the 13th century. Once faithful and generous leaders of their people, the ruling members of the High Council were twisted in form and spirit, and guided their followers down a darker path. Ruling from the shadows and speaking only through ensorcelled priests, these corrupted holy men abused their positions and misguide the faithful into attacking those who followed the &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt;. Their betrayal did not go unrewarded by Mephisto, who transformed them into &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s, granting them abilities far beyond their mortal followers. As demons, the Council members were zealous, and served their new master without question. However, the Council was defeated by a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20II\"&gt;group of heroes&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231264\"&gt;1264&lt;/a&gt;, as they fought their way through Travincal.\nThis was not the end of the Council however. Now demons, they were able to reform in Hell, and became the new &lt;a href=\"Fell%20Council\"&gt;Fell Council&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nDiablo II.\nThe High Council appears as &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\", and must be slain to complete the &lt;a href=\"Blackened%20Temple%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;\"Blackened Temple\"&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;. It consists of five &lt;a href=\"Council%20Member\"&gt;Council Member&lt;/a&gt;s. When the High Council has been destroyed, &lt;a href=\"Zakarum%20Zealots\"&gt;Zakarum Zealots&lt;/a&gt; will no longer attack but instead flee when a player approaches.\nCouncil Members reappear in , appearing as &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"minion\"&gt;minion&lt;/a&gt;s. Players encounter another pack of Council Members led by &lt;a href=\"Bartuc%20the%20Bloody\"&gt;Bartuc the Bloody&lt;/a&gt;. However, these do not appear to be members of the High Council proper, given the distance between locations and context.\nDiablo IV.\nMembers of the High Council reappear in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", now part of the &lt;a href=\"Fell%20Council\"&gt;Fell Council&lt;/a&gt;."}
