{"id": "30141", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30141", "title": "Ranslor's Folly", "text": "Ranslor's Folly are &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"bracers\"&gt;bracers&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", available at &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 70 starting in &lt;a href=\"Season\"&gt;Season&lt;/a&gt; 3. \nThe unique affix makes &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Twister\"&gt;Energy Twister&lt;/a&gt; an effective &lt;a href=\"Crowd%20Control\"&gt;Crowd Control&lt;/a&gt; skill. Multiple Twisters do not grant extra pulls, each enemy becoming immune to the Ranslor's Folly effects (from the same Wizard) for 5 seconds after being pulled.\nDevelopment.\nThese bracers were previously known as \"Lucky Bowman's Armscales\". Some of the stats were the same, but the item description was different, reading as follows:\nRanslor's Folly were originally planned to be introduced during &lt;a href=\"Season\"&gt;Season&lt;/a&gt; Two, but not released in &lt;a href=\"Patch%202.1.2%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Patch 2.1.2&lt;/a&gt;, with taking their place as a &lt;a href=\"Wizard\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt;-specific Seasonal item. The bracers appeared in Season Three instead, after which they became available permanently for all characters."}
