{"id": "16534", "revid": "3459498", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16534", "title": "Rashim", "text": "Rashim was an inhabitant of &lt;a href=\"Hashir\"&gt;Hashir&lt;/a&gt;. Rashim had been an apprentice to a merchant of Hashir and he therefore had some knowledge of the towns and cities surrounding Hashir. \nAfter the arrival of &lt;a href=\"Uldyssian\"&gt;Uldyssian's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Edyrem\"&gt;Edyrem&lt;/a&gt;, Rashim joined their ranks. Rashim eventually became one of the unofficial commanders of the Edyrem, along with &lt;a href=\"Saron\"&gt;Saron&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Timeon\"&gt;Timeon&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "46549", "revid": "51979909", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46549", "title": "Rashta", "text": "Rashta Reborn is a &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Alcarnus\"&gt;Alcarnus&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Stronghold\"&gt;Stronghold&lt;/a&gt;. She is a mad surgeon who became &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; after investigating &lt;a href=\"Alcarnus\"&gt;Alcarnus&lt;/a&gt;'s plague.\nBiography.\nRashta was a surgeon investigating Alcarnus's plague. During her studies, she fell into madness and started to think the plague will become an absolute weapon which she wanted to use.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231336\"&gt;1336&lt;/a&gt;, Rashta fought with The Wanderer and was killed by them. However, she was raised from the dead, only to be killed again."}
{"id": "42627", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42627", "title": "Rasplet", "text": "Rasplets are a type of &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; that inhabit the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Misery\"&gt;Forest of Misery&lt;/a&gt;. Alongside the &lt;a href=\"Gnarled%20Pawn\"&gt;Gnarled Pawn&lt;/a&gt;s, they are demons who've failed &lt;a href=\"Skarn\"&gt;Skarn&lt;/a&gt;, and had their bodies fused with parts of the realm as punishment.\nLore.\nExistence as a rasplet is punishment for minions of &lt;a href=\"Skarn\"&gt;Skarn&lt;/a&gt; seeking territory of their own. Reborn from the jagged pines that abut the plains of torment, rasplets swipe at intruders with barbed claws, or spew spiny pieces of themselves in the hope that the flesh of their kills can reconstitute their old bodies. Because of their part plant nature they can hide in the ground and disguise themselves as one of the barren plants of the Forest of Misery, to lay in ambush.\nRasplets come in three variants"}
