{"id": "52264", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52264", "title": "Rathma's Gift", "text": "Rathma's Gift is an exploration &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; event in &lt;a href=\"Act%20V%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act V&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It takes place in &lt;a href=\"Briarthorn%20Cemetery\"&gt;Briarthorn Cemetery&lt;/a&gt;, where 5 Death Prisons are scattered around the graveyard and must be destroyed.\nA Death Prison is a small metallic object enclosing an orb of blue undead energy. Each of them is guarded by two &lt;a href=\"Death%20Maiden\"&gt;Death Maiden&lt;/a&gt;s and several &lt;a href=\"Summoned%20Archer\"&gt;Summoned Archer&lt;/a&gt;s, among the usual monsters of the zone. Channeling uninterrupted on one destroys it, summoning three shadowy Skeletal Minions to join the party. They do not do a lot of damage but can distract enemies to some degree. Destroying the last Death Prison releases all of them to their final death in a burst of blue energy, awarding gold and experience."}
