{"id": "46531", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46531", "title": "Rathma's Prophecy", "text": "Rathma's Prophecy is a &lt;a href=\"prophecy\"&gt;prophecy&lt;/a&gt; imparted to &lt;a href=\"Rathma\"&gt;Rathma&lt;/a&gt;. \nLore.\nThe origins of the prophecy date back to before &lt;a href=\"the%20Purge\"&gt;the Purge&lt;/a&gt;. It came to Rathma in dreams; shattered images of the end of &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;, carried to him by the scales of &lt;a href=\"Trag%27Oul\"&gt;Trag'Oul&lt;/a&gt;. The thoughts of Rathma and Trag'Oul met, and they were able to piece together the elements of the prophecy. Rathma put it down in order.\nThe prophecy was believed to foretell the rise of the &lt;a href=\"Prime%20Evils\"&gt;Prime Evils&lt;/a&gt;, the return of &lt;a href=\"Lilith\"&gt;Lilith&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Inarius\"&gt;Inarius&lt;/a&gt;, and the doom of &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;. Rathma was again tormented by his visions sometime during or before the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Enmity\"&gt;Great Enmity&lt;/a&gt;. This time, Rathma codified the prophecy into written form.\nInarius became aware of the prophecy sometime after forming the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20Light\"&gt;Cathedral of Light&lt;/a&gt;. The \"light piercing hatred's heart\" line was seized upon by Inarius, who claimed that it was proof he was fated to kill Lilith. The Cathedral's priests went on about the prophecy \"ad nauseum\", and it was claimed that by this act, Inarius would be given the means to ascend to &lt;a href=\"Heaven\"&gt;Heaven&lt;/a&gt;, and bring the faithful with him. Rathma used the &lt;a href=\"Key%20to%20Hell\"&gt;Key to Hell&lt;/a&gt; to seal the &lt;a href=\"Gates%20to%20Hell\"&gt;Gates to Hell&lt;/a&gt;, but knew it was only a matter of time before Inarius came to him, demanding the key.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231336\"&gt;1336&lt;/a&gt;, Inarius journeyed into the &lt;a href=\"Necropolis%20of%20the%20Firstborn\"&gt;Necropolis of the Firstborn&lt;/a&gt; to confront Rathma; a confrontation that resulted in Rathma's &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt; at the hands of his father. Inarius returned to the surface and placed the prophecy in the Cathedral's gospel, and made it seem like he was the hero to save &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;ity. \nTranscript.\nBurned Parchment.\nAnother fragment of the prophecy, known as the \"&lt;a href=\"Burned%20Parchment\"&gt;Burned Parchment&lt;/a&gt;\", can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Tormented%20Ruins\"&gt;Tormented Ruins&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;:\nPossible Interpretations.\nI saw my corpse, and from my mouth crawled Hatred \n\"A father burned his children on a pyre,\"\nand a mother molded a new age from the ashes,\nI saw the weak made strong,\na pack of lambs feasting on wolves,\nTears of blood rained on a desert jewel, \nand the way to Hell was torn asunder, \nThen came a spear of light, piercing Hatred's heart,\nAnd he who was bound in chains was set free\nI saw a serpent coiling in the fires of the Eternal Conflict\na wise man with seven arms\nI saw a child give birth to a mother, \n...as Hatred\u2019s sun set and that of Terror and Destruction dawned. "}
