{"id": "39132", "revid": "47177037", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39132", "title": "Ravens", "text": "Ravens\u00a0is a Companion skill used by\u00a0\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", inspired by the classic Raven minions.\nIn-game.\nThis skill passively summons several ravens that cannot be attacked by enemies and do not block enemy pathing. Each Raven will periodically dive and attack a single foe for moderate damage. \nRavens share the Druid's basic offensive stats, including those gained from passive talents. Their attacks have zero &lt;a href=\"Proc%20Coefficient\"&gt;Proc Coefficient&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen activated, a massive murder of Ravens will perform a one-time attack on the target area, hitting each enemy within it once, dealing high damage and placing a fixed amount of Vulnerability. This Vulnerability stacks with any other, adding up and persisting until removed, but only adds to the total Vulnerable Life pool and does not increase the damage bonus (it's fixed at 30%).\nThis skill can be used in any Shapeshifting form, and does not change the Druid's current form.\nTalents and effects that empower skills do apply to the Ravens, both passively and actively."}
