{"id": "9187", "revid": "43723075", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9187", "title": "Ray of Frost", "text": "Ray of Frost\u00a0is a Cold spell used by\u00a0s\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0\"seemingly inspired by &lt;a href=\"Arctic%20Blast\"&gt;Arctic Blast&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nRay of Frost forms an instant beam that hits the first enemy in its path, as well as other enemies within 5 yards of the target, for &lt;a href=\"Cold\"&gt;Cold&lt;/a&gt; damage per tick, &lt;a href=\"chill\"&gt;chill&lt;/a&gt;ing\u00a0them down for as long as the beam is channeled. While the Wizard continues channeling the beam, its damage grows by 405% damage as Cold per tick, reaching maximum output over 2 ticks, normally 2 seconds (1240% as Cold per tick). Stopping the channeling will reset this bonus.\nThe beam has limited range, roughly 50 yards, and while channeling, the Wizard cannot move.\nIt is the only Wizard direct damaging skill that cannot change its damage type.\nDevelopment.\nBefore patch 2.0, Ray of Frost was a single-target spell. Snow Blast used to grow in power over time instead of increasing damage taken by the target.\nPrior to Patch 2.1, it did not have a channeling-based buff."}
{"id": "37559", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37559", "title": "Ray of Frost (Diablo Immortal)", "text": "Ray of Frost is a skill in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". A beam of frost shoots out from the Wizard. Press the button once to start the beam, press again to stop. It can stack with &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Crystal\"&gt;Ice Crystal&lt;/a&gt;, where if the ray hits the crystal, the crystal will shatter, sending ice shards in all direction."}
{"id": "42606", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42606", "title": "Rayek", "text": "Rayek is a young , best known for his creation of the &lt;a href=\"Helliquary\"&gt;Helliquary&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nRayek hails from &lt;a href=\"Harrogath\"&gt;Harrogath&lt;/a&gt;. A prodigy, Rayek witnessed the horrifying destruction wrought by &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal&lt;/a&gt;. Rayek survived the destruction of &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Arreat\"&gt;Mount Arreat&lt;/a&gt; and subsequent devastation of the &lt;a href=\"Northern%20Steppes\"&gt;Northern Steppes&lt;/a&gt;. He determined that no other people should suffer the way the Barbarians had, and devised a way to prevent &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;ic invasions of &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, Rayek was in &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;, where he met &lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;Deckard Cain&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Charsi\"&gt;Charsi&lt;/a&gt;. With &lt;a href=\"Charsi\"&gt;Charsi&lt;/a&gt;'s help, he created the Helliquary; a wondrous device built to locate particuarly destructive demons and trap their &lt;a href=\"essence\"&gt;essence&lt;/a&gt; when they were slain. Rayek hoped to use his creation to stop demonic incursions before they happened, and prevent the doom that came to his &lt;a href=\"Northern%20Steppes\"&gt;homeland&lt;/a&gt; from ruining other lands.\nPer his construction of the Helliquary, Rayek detected a dark energy emanating from the &lt;a href=\"Einfrinn%20Tree\"&gt;Einfrinn Tree&lt;/a&gt;. While legend held that the tree was planted by King &lt;a href=\"Rakkis\"&gt;Rakkis&lt;/a&gt;, Rayek believed that the tree was as old as &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; itself. Studying the tree, he discovered that the Helliquary had become entangled with the energy leaking from the tree, confirming what he had suspected; that the tree was demonic in nature. More specifically, the tree was holding back a powerful demon, but was growing weaker by the moment. \nRight on time, Rayek met with the hero(es) that Cain had sent his way. Rejecting their suggestion that the tree be destroyed, he suggested that they use the Helliquary on the tree, as it was a conduit of energy. He asked the hero(es) to use their strength, and focus their energy on the tree. The hero(es) passed out, and when they awoke, told Rayek that they'd seen a vision of Westmarch being destroyed by the &lt;a href=\"Wrathborne\"&gt;Wrathborne&lt;/a&gt;. Rayek explained that the tree had given them a vision of the future. To avert it, he suggested that they use the Helliquary. If they added power to it, it would strengthen their connection to the Einfrinn Tree, and with enough power, they could use it as a gateway, taking the fight to the Wrathborne before they were ready. Bidding them to take the Helliquary again, he told them to focus on one of the demons they saw in their vision. The hero(es) obliged, and saw the location of &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Herald%20Pyl\"&gt;Chaos Herald Pyl&lt;/a&gt;. Rayek told them to go slay the demon, and bring him its remains. They obliged, and Rayek suggested that they channel the demonic energies into them. The process worked, and he led the hero(es) to Charsi to obtain &lt;a href=\"scoria\"&gt;scoria&lt;/a&gt; to reinforce the device. He told them that they would need to continue to reinforce the Helliquary as such in order to be powerful enough to access the gateway within the tree. He told them to go tell Cain about their vision, while he returned to the tree.\nThe Crimson Slag.\nSome time after &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Nightmares\"&gt;the mists spread on Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Crimson%20Slag\"&gt;Crimson Slag&lt;/a&gt; fell from the sky at the &lt;a href=\"Wolf%20Gate\"&gt;Wolf Gate&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;. Rayek sent a letter to the Shard-seeker, imploring them to investigate it.\nNew Threats.\nWhen &lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;Deckard Cain&lt;/a&gt; went on a journey, he handed his &lt;a href=\"Cain%27s%20Workshop\"&gt;workshop&lt;/a&gt; over to Rayek to look after until he returned. Rayek built an altar in the secret room in the workshop, that would boost the detection ability of the &lt;a href=\"Helliquary\"&gt;Helliquary&lt;/a&gt;. When he tested it, an interference from &lt;a href=\"Bilefen\"&gt;Bilefen&lt;/a&gt; reduced its performance. He then called &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; to help him investigate the interference, and get a sample of it. The Shard-seeker returned with news that the interference originated from a &lt;a href=\"cracks\"&gt;fissure&lt;/a&gt; that was releasing demonic energy.\nWhen Rayek used the Helliquary to scry the source of the energy, it showed the visage of &lt;a href=\"Saarodan%2C%20Sky-Sunderer\"&gt;a demon&lt;/a&gt;. It also revealed similar fissures located at &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wood\"&gt;Dark Wood&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ashwold%20Cemetery\"&gt;Ashwold Cemetery&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Tundra\"&gt;Frozen Tundra&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Shassar%20Sea\"&gt;Shassar Sea&lt;/a&gt;. The other fissures were found to also be emitting demonic energy. Rayek used the Helliquary to scry energy samples from all the fissures, and it revealed in a vision that the six demons responsible for the fissures were in coalition with each other. He decided to name them &lt;a href=\"Hearthrot\"&gt;Hearthrot&lt;/a&gt;, and implored the Shard-seeker to seal them.\nPrecipice of Horror.\nC. &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231273\"&gt;1273&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Terror%20Rift\"&gt;Terror Rift&lt;/a&gt;s began appearing at random over Sanctuary. Rayek explored one of these rifts and extracted a &lt;a href=\"Terror%20Essence\"&gt;sticky substance&lt;/a&gt; from it. When he touched it, he saw a vision of a &lt;a href=\"Oblivion%20Pillar\"&gt;pillar&lt;/a&gt; that acted as a beacon for the rift.\nAge of Unmaking.\nLater, Rayek was plagued with nightmares. He would see different locations twisted and burning red, like they were being swallowed by the Hells. On one such dream,he found himself in a warped &lt;a href=\"Wortham\"&gt;Wortham&lt;/a&gt;. He sent a letter to summon the Shard-seeker, while he went to Wortham to investigate.\nAt Wortham,he found a breach in space, similar to what he saw in his dream. While studying it, the Shard-seeker arrived. They volunteered to enter the breach and put an end to whatever evil laid within. The Shard-seeker was successful and returned with a solid shard of the breach. Rayek took the Terrorwrought Shard, and after studying it, designed a device to access the verge. He gave the blueprint of the device to Charsi to help him build it.\nIn-game.\nRayek is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". He is introduced via the &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"Opening%20the%20Helliquary\"&gt;Opening the Helliquary&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nDevelopment.\nHis name was originally spelt \"Rayoc.\"\nIn early material, it was stated that Rayek hailed from &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Arreat\"&gt;Mount Arreat&lt;/a&gt;, while in the final version, he is said to hail from &lt;a href=\"Harrogath\"&gt;Harrogath&lt;/a&gt;. However, given the close proximity of the two, this is a small difference, if at all.\nIn early material, the Helliquary was stated to have been built by Charsi. In the final version, Rayek is specified to be the developer of the Helliquary, while Charsi only aided him."}
{"id": "44448", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44448", "title": "Rayek's Sealed Letter", "text": "Rayek's Sealed Letter is an item in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is received automatically as part of the \"&lt;a href=\"Terror%27s%20Tide\"&gt;Terror's Tide&lt;/a&gt;\" update, and required to activated \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Chainbreakers\"&gt;The Chainbreakers&lt;/a&gt;\".\nTranscript.\n\"Have &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;you&lt;/a&gt; seen those &lt;a href=\"Crimson%20Slag\"&gt;red boulders&lt;/a&gt; everywhere? One of them landed near the &lt;a href=\"Wolf%20Gate\"&gt;Wolf Gate&lt;/a&gt;, and the &lt;a href=\"Rakkisguard\"&gt;guards&lt;/a&gt; are unbelievably tense. I barely carved off a piece before they chased me away. Now they're clanking around and arguing with people in the street, and my work's even further behind.\" \n\"I have an awful feeling about all the omens we've been seeing. Would you investigate? &lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;Cain&lt;/a&gt; asked &lt;a href=\"Commander%20Kaya\"&gt;Commander Kaya&lt;/a&gt; to put her seal on this letter. It should help you out.\"\n-Rayek\n\"Let the &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt; pass\u2014alone. They've done a lot of good for our city.\"\n-Kaya"}
{"id": "33355", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33355", "title": "Rayeld", "text": "Rayeld the Younger, also known as The Crazed Man, is a priest of &lt;a href=\"Nereza\"&gt;Nereza&lt;/a&gt; inhabiting the &lt;a href=\"Greyhollow%20Island\"&gt;Greyhollow Island&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nSon of the &lt;a href=\"High%20Cleric\"&gt;High Cleric&lt;/a&gt;, Rayeld was preparing since childhood to become the High Cleric himself. Taught by his father that human sacrifices to Nereza are necessary to keep the island free of evil, he awaited the time when he himself would bring offerings. However, when the time came, he could not bring himself to do so. After he performed ritual murders himself, Rayeld became disgusted with what the cult was doing. Doubting his faith, he decided to put an end to sacrifices.\nAt one point, unable to bring himself to kill a girl named &lt;a href=\"Sara\"&gt;Sara&lt;/a&gt; in the name of Nereza, Rayeld murdered his father, fled with the girl (other cultists, shocked by the incident, did not even try to interfere), rushed to the top of the &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Tower\"&gt;Ancient Tower&lt;/a&gt;, and plunged his sacrificial dagger into Nereza's chest. Before she died, he saw the inhuman gaze of her eyes, and realized that Nereza was no goddess, but a &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;, and the evil the sacrifices were to prevent was not from the outside world, but from herself.\nThe dying demon killed Sara with her last breath, and her essence went through Rayeld into the island itself, cursing the land and the priest, condemning him to eternal torment for his sacrilege. Rayeld was welcomed as a hero by his people when they found out what he did, yet he realized that the corruption from Nereza's evil would eventually ravage the island. It indeed happened, the land becoming uninhabitable: any human stepping on its shores would be driven insane, if not killed earlier by the unseen evil force.\nRayeld attempted to contain the evil, not allowing it to expand to other lands. To do so, he erected magical wards and kept Nereza's spirit pacified by rituals and sacrifices (ironically, doing exactly what he was raised for, with the same purpose he once believed to be his path). Losing his sanity, he became known as The Crazed Man, living as a hermit on the island, only rarely to be seen by travelers and sailors coming to the shore (mostly from shipwrecks).\nUsing his knowledge of the binding rituals, Rayeld &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;ally enslaved majority of the creatures on the island, either by prayers, sacrifices, or simply by carving the warding runes into their skin. Though he himself eventually forgot how and why did he do this, he deeply regretted that he was forced to bind living beings to his will. &lt;a href=\"Sasquatch\"&gt;Sasquatch&lt;/a&gt;es, &lt;a href=\"Bone%20Breaker\"&gt;Bone Breaker&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Wildwood%20Bulwark\"&gt;Wildwood Bulwark&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Shipwrecked%20Soul\"&gt;Shipwrecked Soul&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Wood%20Specter\"&gt;Wood Specter&lt;/a&gt;s and (probably) more creatures of the island were all controlled by him. Rayeld even remarks in his records that he cannot remember if Sasquatches were humans turned feral by evil of the island, or he himself turned them into beasts to protect them from Nereza's corruption. &lt;a href=\"Abyssal\"&gt;Abyssal&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Amputator\"&gt;Amputator&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Flesh%20Harvester\"&gt;Flesh Harvester&lt;/a&gt;s, who Rayeld could not control, he battled until forcing them to remain in their &lt;a href=\"Tidal%20Cave\"&gt;caves&lt;/a&gt;, though he soon learned that as long as the sea people's idols are not disturbed, they would not be aggressive in the first place.\nNereza's curse effectively made Rayeld immortal (of which he was perfectly aware), bringing him back from the dead should he be killed, to ensure his eternal torture. The only way to ensure his release would be to cleanse his spirit at the site of Nereza's death.\nIn-game.\nThe Crazed Man is a &lt;a href=\"Super%20Unique\"&gt;Super Unique&lt;/a&gt; foe found on the Greyhollow Island in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", in &lt;a href=\"Adventure%20Mode\"&gt;Adventure Mode&lt;/a&gt; only. He can be found at one of two possible locations: either amidst the bone totems, or in front of the sacrificial altar.\nIn either case, he will not be hostile to the player, and in fact, will not even acknowledge their presence, being busy tending to the binding rituals. If talked to, or if his ritual is interfered with, he will turn hostile.\nIn either case, he will attack by hurling darkfire bolts that deal tremendous damage from afar. He has no other abilities. However, other monsters in the area will protect him, depending on the event.\nHe can also be encountered during the unmarked event atop the &lt;a href=\"Forsaken%20Repose\"&gt;Forsaken Repose&lt;/a&gt;, if player touches any of his satchels (of &lt;a href=\"Testament%20of%20My%20Failure\"&gt;Testament of My Failure&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"tome\"&gt;tome&lt;/a&gt;) after they collect both tomes. This opens a purple portal to the top of &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Tower\"&gt;Ancient Tower&lt;/a&gt;, at the very site where Rayeld killed Nereza. He can then be talked to, and will tell that he waited for a long time for &lt;a href=\"the%20Nephalem\"&gt;the Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; to come to this place since their last visit.\nHe will then ask the Nephalem to cleanse his spirit. The player must first destroy his mortal form at the tower. This will be complicated due to Crazed Man gaining an extra ability to summon a slowly moving broad wall of darkfire, which, if touched by player, will deal significant damage over time. Moreover, he will now hurl darkfire bolts in clusters of three, being hit by all three is enough to kill an adequately geared hero outright.\nIf defeated, his ghost is released, continuing to fight on its own. In spirit form, he gains Illusionist affix, his darkfire bolts are replaced with equally powerful spirit bolts, and instead of the wave of flame, he will launch homing black gouts of spirit fire, which expire after short time.\nKilling him in his spirit form will lift the curse, supposedly liberating his soul, and opening the portal back to the island."}
