{"id": "4647", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4647", "title": "Razorswitch", "text": "Razorswitch is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Jo%20Staff\"&gt;Jo Staff&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlthough its skill bonuses are minimal at best, casters such &lt;a href=\"Sorceress\"&gt;Sorceress&lt;/a&gt;es or &lt;a href=\"Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt;s may find its large &lt;a href=\"mana\"&gt;mana&lt;/a&gt; bonus useful.\nBesides its mana bonus, Razorswitch also gives a rather large boost to &lt;a href=\"Resistances\"&gt;Resistances&lt;/a&gt;, making up for lack of a &lt;a href=\"Shields\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt;. In and &lt;a href=\"Difficulty\"&gt;difficulties&lt;/a&gt;, where resistances are drastically lowered, this could be particularly useful.\nRazorswitch also boasts a high bonus to &lt;a href=\"Faster%20Cast%20Rate\"&gt;Faster Cast Rate&lt;/a&gt;. Sorceresses and Necromancers who specialize in &lt;a href=\"Poison%20and%20Bone%20Spells\"&gt;Poison and Bone Spells&lt;/a&gt; will find this useful, but casters such as &lt;a href=\"Summonmancer\"&gt;Summonmancer&lt;/a&gt;s, that have little use for cast rate, are better off with other weapons more specific to their &lt;a href=\"classes\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt;.\nRazorswitch's other bonuses, i.e. &lt;a href=\"Damage%20reduction\"&gt;Reduction of Magic Damage&lt;/a&gt; and return of Damage taken, are minimal, especially in Nightmare and Hell modes. However, its ability to return damage may be handy when Razorswitch's user is surrounded, causing enemies to flinch after they attack you, and giving the user just enough time to escape or retaliate.\nLike most &lt;a href=\"staves\"&gt;staves&lt;/a&gt;, Razorswitch is not intended for physical fighters, due to its low damage and durability. The only unique staff exempt from this rule is &lt;a href=\"Ribcracker\"&gt;Ribcracker&lt;/a&gt;.\nStats.\nTwo-Hand Damage: 6 to 21\nDurability: 20 of 20\nRequired Strength: 25\nRequired Level: 28\nStaff Class - Fast Attack Speed"}
