{"id": "26453", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26453", "title": "Reaper's Fear", "text": "Reaper's Fear\u00a0was a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Crafting%20Material\"&gt;Legendary Crafting Material&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It only dropped from\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Malthael\"&gt;Malthael&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and was required to craft the &lt;a href=\"Reaper%27s%20Wraps\"&gt;Reaper's Wraps&lt;/a&gt; bracers. It has an\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Item%20Level\"&gt;Item Level&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0of 1, can be stacked up to 1000 times, and is\u00a0&lt;a href=\"account%20bound\"&gt;account bound&lt;/a&gt;. As of patch 2.0.6, it is no longer necessary (occasionally drops due to a bug), and existing Fears can be sold for 50,000 gold.\nIn the early versions of the game, it was bugged, and it was nearly impossible to obtain this ingredient. However, with Malthael being the hardest boss in game (both in terms of difficulty and accessibility), it was not a trivial task to farm the Reaper's Fear even after the fix.\n\"Only one who has gazed into the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Abyss\"&gt;black abyss&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt; could experience such fear.\""}
{"id": "25980", "revid": "25771421", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=25980", "title": "Reaper's Wraps", "text": "Reaper's Wraps\u00a0are &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"bracers\"&gt;bracers&lt;/a&gt; in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". They require a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Character%20Level\"&gt;Character Level&lt;/a&gt; of\u00a070 to wear.\nDue to the special affix, these may be considered valuable for builds relying on heavy resource management.\nTo craft these, one would need Plan: Reaper's Wraps, which only drops from &lt;a href=\"Malthael\"&gt;Malthael&lt;/a&gt;, but the drop is guaranteed if you do not have it yet. It is the only level 70 craftable item with a guaranteed drop recipe.\u00a0\nDespite the official Game Guide tooltip saying these bracers have 8 extra properties, they actually have a limit of just five, like most items in game.\nAs of patch 2.6.9, the effect has a 2 second &lt;a href=\"cooldown\"&gt;cooldown&lt;/a&gt;, i.e. it cannot grant resources more than once every 2 seconds.\nCrafting.\nCrafting Reaper's Wraps requires, in addition to plans, 64000 &lt;a href=\"gold\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt;, 20 &lt;a href=\"Reusable%20Parts\"&gt;Reusable Parts&lt;/a&gt;, 20 &lt;a href=\"Arcane%20Dust\"&gt;Arcane Dust&lt;/a&gt;, 30 &lt;a href=\"Veiled%20Crystal\"&gt;Veiled Crystal&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Caldeum%20Nightshade\"&gt;Caldeum Nightshade&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Arreat%20War%20Tapestry\"&gt;Arreat War Tapestry&lt;/a&gt;.\nBefore patch 2.0.6., these bracers also required\u00a0a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Reaper%27s%20Fear\"&gt;Reaper's Fear&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0legendary ingredient, dropped from Malthael."}
