{"id": "50962", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50962", "title": "Rebirth", "text": "Rebirth is the process by which a non-Seasonal character can be turned into a &lt;a href=\"Season\"&gt;Season&lt;/a&gt;al one in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". They are reset to level 1 with no gear or other progression, just like any other new Seasonal character. This allows a a pre-existing character to join the Season, and allows a player who already has the maximum number of characters to participate without deleting and recreating any characters.\nThis option has been available since Season 5.\nUsage.\nThe Rebirth option is shown on the character selection section of the main menu before starting a game. It can only be used on three characters per season. A confirmation box explains the process before completing the rebirth. The player may select \"normal\" Seasonal mode or &lt;a href=\"Solo%20Self%20Found\"&gt;Solo Self Found&lt;/a&gt; mode. Upon accepting, the character will be marked as Seasonal, and all forms of character progress will be reset:\nOnly their choice of name, class, gender, and &lt;a href=\"Hardcore\"&gt;Hardcore&lt;/a&gt; status is preserved. In almost every way it is as if the original character had been deleted, and a new Seasonal one was created with the same character creation choices, with the exception of mailing the previous items.\nNote that many forms of progression are actually stored \"per account\" rather than \"per character\" - or more accurately, per &lt;a href=\"game%20mode\"&gt;game mode&lt;/a&gt; on the account. These aspects, such as &lt;a href=\"Paragon\"&gt;Paragon&lt;/a&gt; levels, &lt;a href=\"artisan\"&gt;artisan&lt;/a&gt; advancement, and the shared &lt;a href=\"stash\"&gt;stash&lt;/a&gt;, are retained by the other non-Seasonal characters. If a player already has other Seasonal characters, the Rebirthed character would even gain the benefits of \"their\" account/mode-level progression, if any."}
{"id": "34867", "revid": "28145144", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34867", "title": "Reborn", "text": "Reborn (known as Shepherds in the beta) are a &lt;a href=\"Demon\"&gt;Demon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; type encountered in the lower levels of the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20the%20Firstborn\"&gt;Temple of the Firstborn&lt;/a&gt; in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn-game.\nReborn are quite rare, and attack almost exclusively as ranged casters. Their primary attack is a volley of several bolts of energy in quick succession. These bolts are fired at very high speed and velocity, and unless the character is already moving, dodging them is extremely hard.\nIn addition, Reborn have the ability to &lt;a href=\"teleport\"&gt;teleport&lt;/a&gt; at will, disappearing into a blue wormhole and then emerging anywhere on the battlefield.\nVisually, they appear very similar to &lt;a href=\"Vidian\"&gt;Vidian&lt;/a&gt; himself; in addition, their name might imply that this is the last stage of &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Cultist\"&gt;Blood Cultist&lt;/a&gt;s' \"ascension\"."}
{"id": "45557", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45557", "title": "Recall a Friend", "text": "Recall a Friend is a gameplay/event feature in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". The event began on March 30, 3:00 a.m. The ability to recall players ends on April 27 at 3:00 a.m. server time, but players will have until May 25 to reach &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;Level&lt;/a&gt; 40 and claim their additional rewards.\nTo recall players, the inviter must be at least Level 30. Each player has a unique code that can be found on the Recall a Friend event page, which can be shared with a friend. Alternatively, one can recall a player via an in-game invitation system located within the event's menu. To be recalled by another player, the inviter must not have logged in to \"Diablo Immortal\" for at least 14 days and are level 20 or higher. Once logged in, input the friend\u2019s code on the Recall a Friend event page. This must be done within 24 hours.\nThe recalling player will receive 10 Recruitment Points the first time they complete each of the following tasks:\nOnce the inviter has accumulated the required number of Recruitment Points, the following rewards can be claimed from the Recall a Friend event menu:\nRecalled players will receive their rewards immediately after accepting the invitation or inputting their friend's code. Recalled players can also receive an additional bounty of rewards if they reach Level 40. Only one code may be redeemed by each recalled player.\nRewards for recalled players:"}
{"id": "42237", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42237", "title": "Recalling the Past", "text": "Recalling the Past is the ninth &lt;a href=\"Library%20of%20Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Library of Zoltun Kulle&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It follows on directly from \"&lt;a href=\"Reforging%20the%20Soul\"&gt;Reforging the Soul&lt;/a&gt;\", and leads directly into the \"&lt;a href=\"Destruction%27s%20End\"&gt;Destruction's End&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"dungeon%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;dungeon&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\n\"With the Spark of Life in hand, the core can be animated once more. At long last, &lt;a href=\"the%20Curator\"&gt;the Curator&lt;/a&gt; holds dominion over the library of &lt;a href=\"Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Zoltun Kulle&lt;/a&gt;.\"\n\"As the wards fall, the Curator is finally free to move throughout the archives. Exactly as promised, he will guide you to the Master's hidden knowledge.\"\n\"Finding the &lt;a href=\"tome\"&gt;tome&lt;/a&gt;, the Curator suggests the two of you abscond to a more secure location: an alcove the master used for reliving memories.\"\n\"The tome of &lt;a href=\"Destruction%27s%20End\"&gt;Destruction's End&lt;/a&gt; lies open. Read its words and transcend them, to a &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Exile\"&gt;time long ago&lt;/a&gt; when the &lt;a href=\"Horadrim\"&gt;Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; pursued the &lt;a href=\"Prime%20Evils\"&gt;Three&lt;/a&gt;.\""}
