{"id": "8320", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8320", "title": "Red Lightning Hose", "text": "The Red Lightning Hose is one of &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;'s signature attack in &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;his&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;appearances&lt;/a&gt;. It is also known as Lightning Inferno. In \"&lt;a href=\"Heroes%20of%20the%20Storm\"&gt;Heroes of the Storm&lt;/a&gt;,\" it's known as Lightning Breath.\nWhen using it, Diablo projects a stream of &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Damage%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage in a fashion much like the &lt;a href=\"Sorceress\"&gt;Sorceress&lt;/a&gt;' and the &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Arctic%20Blast\"&gt;Arctic Blast&lt;/a&gt;. Unlike other spells used by monsters, it deals &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; and Lightning\u00a0damage. Players caught in this deadly stream of destruction must make haste to get out of its path (which can be difficult, as he will usually grab his target directly after initiating the attack). Before Diablo initiates the attack, he raises his right hand in a manner similar to his &lt;a href=\"Cold%20Touch\"&gt;Cold Touch&lt;/a&gt; attack, but his palm does not glow blue. Many players know this attack as Diablo's deadliest skill. Players using shields can block the physical part of this attack.\nThis attack makes a return in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It is seen in Phase 3 in the final duel against Diablo and, unlike his previous incarnation, he takes a deep breath and launches a cone of lightning from his mouth.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", &lt;a href=\"Shumbeel\"&gt;Shumbeel&lt;/a&gt; uses a far weaker variant of this skill as a breath attack.\nTip.\nIn Hell difficulty, if you stand close enough to Diablo, his attack won't hit you because the damage originates past the character."}
