{"id": "40521", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40521", "title": "Reforge Stone", "text": "Reforge Stones feature in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". Players can earn Reforge Stones for extra re-rolls on the magical attribute of an equipment, or purchase Specialized Reforge Stones, which allow players to focus on the item properties they want most. They are purchased using &lt;a href=\"Eternal%20Orb\"&gt;Eternal Orb&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"platinum\"&gt;platinum&lt;/a&gt;, with each stone costing 1000 platinum, and purchased via &lt;a href=\"Yverius\"&gt;Yverius&lt;/a&gt;.\nReforge Stones can only be used on gear of rank or higher.\nA second loadout can be unlocked by reforging 240 times.\nFamilies.\nReforge Stones are divided into 6 families. As of the \"&lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20Manifest\"&gt;Nightmare Manifest&lt;/a&gt;\" update, equipping a gear with 3 stones of the same family grants a bonus magical property specific for the family.\nHistory.\nThe second loadout was added in the update."}
