{"id": "48465", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48465", "title": "Remnant", "text": "Remnants are items associated with &lt;a href=\"Warbands\"&gt;Warbands&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGameplay.\nEach Remnant has an associated warband room type (Protector, Attacker, Support and Survivor). The Remnant's effects are only active when assigned to that room type.\nRemnant Sets.\nRemnants can be obtained from &lt;a href=\"Purge%20the%20Depths\"&gt;Purge the Depths&lt;/a&gt;. After finishing a run, the Remnants collected are grouped into a Remnant Set and added to the Remnant Sets of your warband. Once created, remnant sets cannot be modified, and the only possible operations on them are equipping, locking/unlocking and deleting them.\nIn the Warband interface, every Remnant Set is shown at once, however the display may be confusing as the Remnants within a set are ordered such that the ones associated with the currently selected room type are first on the list and all the others are darkened. Furthermore even the sets themselves are rearranged such that the sets with the most Remnants for the current room type are at the top."}
