{"id": "52181", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52181", "title": "Research Problems", "text": "Research Problems is an &lt;a href=\"Event%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;event&lt;/a&gt; that takes place within the &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Marsh\"&gt;Blood Marsh&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Act%20V%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act V&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nA researcher has been attempting to stop a plague in the marsh, and works in a vaguely sheltered area formed by the ruin of a small building. He is being attacked by &lt;a href=\"Shrieking%20Terror\"&gt;Shrieking Terror&lt;/a&gt;s as &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; approaches, and they must be killed. After a brief conversation, the smell of his experiments on &lt;a href=\"Boggit\"&gt;Boggit&lt;/a&gt; corpses attracts a swarm of them, along with a few &lt;a href=\"Diseased%20Bogan\"&gt;Diseased Bogan&lt;/a&gt;s. Culling them all finishes the event.\nIf he is kept alive, he drops an extra item and some gold piles in addition to the standard gold/experience event reward."}
