{"id": "7823", "revid": "865253", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7823", "title": "Resist", "text": ""}
{"id": "4145", "revid": "25014340", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4145", "title": "Resist Cold", "text": "Resist Cold is a &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"The splendor of absolute devotion is all the warmth and comfort a Paladin requires. Embraced deep within the shelter of this aura, the faithful need never fear the frost.\"\nGeneral Information.\nWhile active, this aura grants the user and nearby allies a large portion of extra Cold resistance, as well as a bonus to maximum Cold resist, both values increasing per level.\nWhen the skill is inactive, the player still receives half of this latter bonus, rounded down (and only counting hard skill points, not points given by equipment). The maximum cap of 95% Resist still applies. Actual resistance is not affected, just\u00a0\"maximum\" resist.\u00a0\nNote that the D2R in-game skill desc is wrong about it, using .5% resolution which is not actually used by the engine due to the value being rounded down to int(.blvl/2) in Skills.txt calc. Also, the desc is wrongly showing exactly the same max resist values for next level (they work as expected though)."}
{"id": "4144", "revid": "25014340", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4144", "title": "Resist Fire", "text": "Resist Fire is a &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"Shrouding himself in his devotions, the fervent servant of the &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt; can walk a lake of fire and feel only the comforting warmth of his convictions. A Paladin can withstand the might of a fierce conflagration if his piety is strong enough.\"\nGeneral Information.\nWhile active, this aura grants the user and nearby allies a large portion of extra Fire resistance, as well as a bonus to maximum Fire resist, both values increasing per level.\nWhen the skill is inactive, the player still receives half of this latter bonus, rounded down (and only counting hard skill points, not points given by equipment). The maximum cap of 95% Resist still applies. Actual resistance is not affected, just maximum resist.\nNote that the D2R in-game skill desc is wrong about it, using .5% resolution which is not actually used by the engine due to the value being rounded down to int(.blvl/2) in Skills.txt calc. Also, the desc is wrongly showing exactly the same max resist values for next level (they work as expected though).\nThe &lt;a href=\"Flickering%20Flame%20Rune%20Word\"&gt;Flickering Flame Rune Word&lt;/a&gt; gives the aura to the wielder of the helmet."}
{"id": "4146", "revid": "25014340", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4146", "title": "Resist Lightning", "text": "Resist Lightning is a &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"Even the elements of nature must yield before the glory of the &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt;. When a knight of Zakarum has manifested this aura, he and his allies undergo a lessening of their body's natural conductivity, protecting them from attacks empowered by electricity.\"\nGeneral Information.\nWhile active, this aura grants the user and nearby allies a large portion of extra Lightning resistance, as well as a bonus to maximum Lightning resist, both values increasing per level.\nWhen the skill is inactive, the player still receives half of this latter bonus, rounded down (and only counting hard skill points, not points given by equipment). The maximum cap of 95% Resist still applies. Actual resistance is not affected, just maximum resist.\nNote that the D2R in-game skill desc is wrong about it, using .5% resolution which is not actually used by the engine due to the value being rounded down to int(.blvl/2) in Skills.txt calc. Also, the desc is wrongly showing exactly the same max resist values for next level (they work as expected though)."}
