{"id": "26711", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26711", "title": "Resurrection", "text": "Resurrection is an &lt;a href=\"event%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;event&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Act%20V%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act V&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It occurs in the &lt;a href=\"Occupied%20Ruins\"&gt;Occupied Ruins&lt;/a&gt; within the &lt;a href=\"Battlefields%20of%20Eternity\"&gt;Battlefields of Eternity&lt;/a&gt;, which always houses either this event or &lt;a href=\"The%20Demon%20Cache\"&gt;The Demon Cache&lt;/a&gt;. A &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; is sometimes offered to complete Resurrection.\nIn the ruins, players might encounter an &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt; fighting back the demonic horde. He will ask for assistance in stopping the &lt;a href=\"Barbed%20Lurker\"&gt;Barbed Lurker&lt;/a&gt; demon lord &lt;a href=\"Tarthess\"&gt;Tarthess&lt;/a&gt;, who is trying to resurrect its ancestor and master buried nearby. The monster is found in the end of the bridge, past several &lt;a href=\"Barbed%20Lurker\"&gt;Barbed Lurker&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Warscarred%20Marauder\"&gt;Warscarred Marauder&lt;/a&gt;s. Killing it will finish the event, and the angel will thank &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; for help.\nObjectives.\nIn addition to the usual gold and experience reward, there is usually a &lt;a href=\"Resplendent%20Chest\"&gt;Resplendent Chest&lt;/a&gt; just after Tarthess is encountered, but it is independent from the event."}
{"id": "27678", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27678", "title": "Resurrection (Event)", "text": ""}
{"id": "42667", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42667", "title": "Resurrection Stone", "text": "The Resurrection Stone is an item in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nThe Stone is acquired during the &lt;a href=\"Wortham\"&gt;Wortham&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;line. It starts with one charge (or replenishes after use) through slaying &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s, up to a maximum of three charges.\nIf the player has any charges on their Stone when they die in the open world, they will be given the option to use a charge or return to their last unlocked hub. If the Stone is used, the character gains a short window of invulnerability. However, Resurrection Stones can't be used in the &lt;a href=\"Battleground\"&gt;Battleground&lt;/a&gt;, in Rifts, or the &lt;a href=\"Helliquary\"&gt;Helliquary&lt;/a&gt;.\nOf note, players can resurrect each other in the open world. If a player's character is restored to life in this manner, it does not use a Resurrection Stone charge."}
