{"id": "44540", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44540", "title": "Karshun", "text": " is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; seen in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBiography.\nKarshun was a member of the &lt;a href=\"Taan\"&gt;Taan&lt;/a&gt;, and studied at the &lt;a href=\"Taan%20Star%20Observatory\"&gt;Taan Star Observatory&lt;/a&gt;. He was a prodigious student, and at a point accurately predicted and deflected projectiles for seven days at a stretch during prognostication training.\nHe became friends with another practitioner called &lt;a href=\"Othva\"&gt;Othva&lt;/a&gt;. In their fifth year, they built the &lt;a href=\"Astral%20Bloom\"&gt;Astral Bloom&lt;/a&gt;; an artifact that could greatly boost &lt;a href=\"divination\"&gt;divination&lt;/a&gt; through the &lt;a href=\"Astral%20Realm\"&gt;Astral Realm&lt;/a&gt;. Unfortunately, the device needed a long time to charge. Othva discovered that by binding &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s to it, the charge time could be reduced. Karshun caught Othva just after he sacrificed some of their colleagues and was aghast at the act. Both of them came to blows over it. Both of them were judged and exiled from the Taan and their device was sealed.\nKarshun later became an apprentice of &lt;a href=\"Ormus\"&gt;Ormus&lt;/a&gt;. His master made an acquaintance of &lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;Deckard Cain&lt;/a&gt;, who together with a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20II\"&gt;group of heroes&lt;/a&gt; were hunting the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Evil\"&gt;Great Evil&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Mephisto\"&gt;Mephisto&lt;/a&gt;. Though Ormus originally had a dim view of Cain and his companions, they later became friends.\nThrough this relationship, Karshun came to be on friendly terms with Cain.\nStarsign.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"End%20of%20Days\"&gt;End of Days&lt;/a&gt; imminent, Cain sought the help of &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;'s leadership to make measures to prevent this doom, but was rebuffed. He then sent a letter to Ormus requesting help. Busy with other commitments Ormus sent Karshun in his stead.\nHe then sent a letter to Ormus requesting help. Busy with other commitments, Ormus sent Karshun in his stead. On the journey, at the gulf before Westmarch, the ship captain picked up some drowned corpses from the sea, intending to give them a proper burial once they reach land. \nUpon arriving Westmarch, different sea creatures started crawling out of the bodies and under the boat to attack the crew, causing them to panic. Karshun stayed back to clear the infestation.infestation.\nAid came in the form of &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt;,who was sent to retrieve him on Cain's behalf. After a warm reunion, they proceeded to &lt;a href=\"Cain%27s%20Workshop\"&gt;Cain's Workshop&lt;/a&gt; to set up a divination ritual, after sending the Shard-seeker to alert the Westmarch guards of the situation.\nAstral Vision.\nUsing an artifact of his creation; the &lt;a href=\"Astral%20Anchor\"&gt;Astral Anchor&lt;/a&gt;, Karshun intended to, together with the Shard-seeker, scry the activities of &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Diablo's cultists&lt;/a&gt; using the &lt;a href=\"Astral%20Realm\"&gt;Astral Realm&lt;/a&gt; as astral projections. Their scrying led them to a &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint%20Keep\"&gt;castle grounds&lt;/a&gt;, where a battle was going on between Terror cultists and guards in uniforms similar to Westmarch guards.\nA portal opens, revealing &lt;a href=\"Akinees\"&gt;two&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Viv%20Mesztros\"&gt;individuals&lt;/a&gt; accompanied by &lt;a href=\"Bride%20of%20Hell\"&gt;a mysterious woman&lt;/a&gt;, who promised them rewards from &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt; if they could bring &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;the \"shard\"&lt;/a&gt; to him. Unfortunately, the woman sensed the watchful eyes of intruders from \"beyond the veil\", an hurled a spell at their projections, injuring Karshun from the backlash.\nKarshun made a hasty retreat to the Astral Realm with his companion. Unfortunately, the Bride of Hell projected cultists into the Astral Realm to stop them. With their astral projection unstable because of the backlash, they had to find a way to quickly return to their bodies lest the connection between their &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s and bodies be severed.\nHis companion defended him while he tried to open a Tear back to their bodies, with only slight success. As a last ditch effort, The Bride summoned &lt;a href=\"Ifriss%20the%20Destroyer\"&gt;Ifriss the Destroyer&lt;/a&gt; directly into the Astral Realm to stop them. They escaped, but it was a close call.\nKarshun revealed all the was able to decipher from the vision; that the Cult of Terror had invaded a place called &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint\"&gt;Stormpoint&lt;/a&gt;, and they were looking for a shard of the Worldstone.\nCain carried Karshun to see a healer, while bidding the Shard-seeker to journey to Stormpoint.\nTerror Ascending.\nThe Shard-seeker returned with bad news; they were able to find the shard, but it was stolen by cultists while they tried to defend &lt;a href=\"Esmund\"&gt;two&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Fern\"&gt;orphans&lt;/a&gt; from more cultists, and that the shard was now in the hands of the Bride of Hell.\nDestruction's Wake.\nKarshun and Cain deduced how to use the &lt;a href=\"Pathstone\"&gt;Pathstone&lt;/a&gt;. However, there was a rumor Cain wished to investigate, which led to him departing Westmarch. Cain gave Karshun his &lt;a href=\"Cain%27s%20Workshop\"&gt;workshop&lt;/a&gt; to use until his return. He offered comfort to the Shard-seeker as they watched Cain depart, before he instructed the &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt; on how to use it to navigate the &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Sea\"&gt;Forgotten Sea&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nKarshun was introduced in the &lt;a href=\"Terror%27s%20Tide\"&gt;Terror's Tide&lt;/a&gt; quest &lt;a href=\"Starsign\"&gt;Starsign&lt;/a&gt;, where he plays a major role. He makes short appearances in later quests. When accompanying the player, he attacks with magic missiles and arcane torrents.\nPersonality and Traits.\nAbilities.\nKarshun is an accomplished mage, and was once part of the &lt;a href=\"Yshari%20Sanctum\"&gt;Yshari Sanctum&lt;/a&gt;. He is especially proficient in divination."}
{"id": "54449", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54449", "title": "Karshun and the Taan", "text": " is a manuscript presumably written by &lt;a href=\"Karshun\"&gt;Karshun&lt;/a&gt;. It is found in an alcove along the booby trapped hallways of the &lt;a href=\"Taan%20Star%20Observatory\"&gt;Taan Star Observatory&lt;/a&gt; during the \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"Elite%20Quest\"&gt;Elite Quest&lt;/a&gt; \"\"&lt;a href=\"The%20Astral%20Bloom\"&gt;The Astral Bloom&lt;/a&gt;\"\". After being read,it is stored in the \"Notes\" section of the &lt;a href=\"Adventurer%27s%20Chronicle\"&gt;Adventurer's Chronicle&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "34788", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34788", "title": "Karybdus", "text": "Karybdus was a &lt;a href=\"Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt;. He was gray-eyed, with short gray hair, and wore &lt;a href=\"armor\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt; made of bone and metal that gave him a bit of a reptilian look. He was well versed in &lt;a href=\"necromancy\"&gt;necromancy&lt;/a&gt;, particularly adept in the &lt;a href=\"life%20tap\"&gt;life tap&lt;/a&gt; technique, and always planned out his options in advance.\nBiography.\nEarly Service.\nKarybdus was highly regarded by the &lt;a href=\"Priests%20of%20Rathma\"&gt;Priests of Rathma&lt;/a&gt;. His deeds were regarded as examples of the ultimate dedication to the &lt;a href=\"Balance%20%28Philosophy%29\"&gt;Balance&lt;/a&gt;. Over his years, his foes included tyrants, spellcasters, and &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s, all of which he triumphed against. This included the &lt;a href=\"Vizjerei\"&gt;Vizjerei&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Armin%20Ra\"&gt;Armin Ra&lt;/a&gt;. It was in preparation for this battle that Karybdus fashioned his armor. It was also a battle that he won. Within his order, he perfected many of the spells the priests used. He had some respect for &lt;a href=\"Zayl\"&gt;Zayl&lt;/a&gt;, whose parents he had fought beside before he was even born, and whom he briefly resurrected after Zayl had accidentally killed them. By the year &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231265\"&gt;1265&lt;/a&gt;, Karybdus was over 100 years old, his stamina and drive fueled by his desire to see &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; in perfect balance. Over the years, he lost bits and pieces of his &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;, but was able to replenish it from \"those who no longer needed it.\"\nStill, Karybdus was disturbed. The Priests of Rathma had fought the forces of the &lt;a href=\"Prime%20Evils\"&gt;Prime Evils&lt;/a&gt; for centuries in their bid to maintain the Balance. He believed that the priesthood's actions had pushed the Balance too far to the &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt;, and that a dark act had to be carried out to set the Balance right.\nMoon of the Spider.\nNot long after the destruction of the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt;, Karybdus resurrected King &lt;a href=\"Cornelius\"&gt;Cornelius&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;, in exchange for getting his son, &lt;a href=\"Justinian%20IV\"&gt;Justinian IV&lt;/a&gt;, under his control, or at least, cooperating with his plan. Karybdus also worked with &lt;a href=\"Aldric%20Jitan\"&gt;Aldric Jitan&lt;/a&gt;, a noble who hoped to rule &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;, to retrieve the &lt;a href=\"Moon%20of%20the%20Spider%20%28item%29\"&gt;Moon of the Spider&lt;/a&gt;. He was put off by the noble, especially after he'd destroyed several manuscripts from his own library, but accepted that Jitan was necessary for the completion of his plans. He knew that Jitan would get nowhere with the artifact, but leading him on, performed a ritual, releasing some of the &lt;a href=\"Children%20of%20Astrogha\"&gt;Children of Astrogha&lt;/a&gt; from the object, which killed Jitan's men-at-arms who were standing nearby. All Jitan had to do was master the relic before the time of convergence with the moon. He also told him of an enemy, informing him that he could be a threat to Jitan's plans. \nThe attack failed, but Karybdus at least learned that his foe was Zayl, much to his aggravation. He considered bringing Zayl into the fold, but decided against it, reasoning that Zayl was too loyal to the concept of the Balance the Priests preached to join him. Likewise, he had to deal with Jitan as well, who was pressing him on the issue of both the relic, and of Zayl himself. Karybdus soothed the noble's concerns on both issues. He abducted &lt;a href=\"Salane%20Nasardo\"&gt;Salane Nasardo&lt;/a&gt;, a noble whom Zayl had been protecting, in order for the ritual to be conducted. He gave her half-hearted apologies for his actions, stating that the Balance had to be maintained. He took Salane to a hill overlooking &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;, where the ritual would be conducted. Zayl and &lt;a href=\"Sardak%20Nasardo\"&gt;Sardak Nasardo&lt;/a&gt; were able to save her, albeit at the cost of Sardak's life. It wasn't really a loss for Zayl however, for as Salane's brother, Sardak's &lt;a href=\"blood\"&gt;blood&lt;/a&gt; would do just as well. Furthermore, the Children of Astrogha were able to capture Zayl and bring him to Karybdus. Zayl demanded to know what could have caused Karybdus to forsake the Balance, but as Karybdus explained, he was still dedicated to it, explaining his view on how his acts at Westmarch would correct the Balance.\nThe ritual was conducted, and &lt;a href=\"Astrogha\"&gt;Astrogha&lt;/a&gt; himself was summoned into Sanctuary, killing Jitan, and using his body as a host. Karybdus offered to kill Zayl, but Astrogha wanted him preserved, and directed his minions against &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;. Karybdus planned to eventually betray Astrogha, but not after his minions had done their work. However, his plans went awry, as Astrogha decided to take Zayl as his host, for after all, a Necromancer in the thrall of a demon would be a powerful host indeed. Karybdus bided his time, realizing that he had underestimated Astrogha's influence within Sanctuary. Still, he'd let him take Zayl as a host for now. He secretly cast life tap\u2014Astrogha could take Zayl's body, but he'd be a far weaker host than the demon had anticipated. Once the Balance was corrected, he'd send Astrogha right back to &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe was interrupted by Salane, who arrived to save Zayl, but Karybdus easily incapacitated her. However, she was able to return Zayl's dagger to him, which gave him the power he needed to resist Astrogha's attempts at possession. He turned the specter of a &lt;a href=\"wendigo\"&gt;wendigo&lt;/a&gt; on him, which ripped out some of Karybdus's soul. Karybdus was harmed, but not slain; after all, this was not the first time his soul had been damaged. However, Salane plunged Karybdus's own dagger into the back of his neck. Karybdus clawed at the gaping wound, while Salane and Zayl were able to banish Astrogha. Karybdus cried out, in rage, claiming that the Balance may never be set right. Equally enraged, Zayl stabbed Karybdus with his own dagger, this time through the heart. He shoved his body into the portal that had banished Astrogha from Sanctuary."}
{"id": "23673", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23673", "title": "Karyna", "text": "Karyna appears in the &lt;a href=\"Act%20I%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;first act&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". \nShe has the gift of foresight, but also a knack for getting into trouble.\nBiography.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231285\"&gt;1285&lt;/a&gt;, Karyna was in the highlands near &lt;a href=\"Wortham\"&gt;Wortham&lt;/a&gt;. She saw members of the &lt;a href=\"Coven\"&gt;Coven&lt;/a&gt; dragging a &lt;a href=\"Tyrael\"&gt;man&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Leoric\"&gt;Leoric&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Leoric%27s%20Manor\"&gt;manor&lt;/a&gt;. After this, she stole a staff from a &lt;a href=\"khazra\"&gt;khazra&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Goatman%20Shaman\"&gt;shaman&lt;/a&gt;, which she left in her cart. The khazra went mad, and chased her into the &lt;a href=\"Caverns%20of%20Araneae\"&gt;Caverns of Araneae&lt;/a&gt;. There, she was ensared by &lt;a href=\"Queen%20Araneae\"&gt;Queen Araneae&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; found Karyna encased in webbing. They were able to free her from the webs, and slew Aranae herself. They led Karyna out of the caves, and asked about a prisoner of the Coven. Karyna told them of the man she'd seen earlier, and the staff she'd stolen.\nIn-game.\nKaryna appears in the \"&lt;a href=\"Trailing%20the%20Coven\"&gt;Trailing the Coven&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;. Players encounter her in the Caverns of Aranae.\nDevelopment.\nKaryna was originally supposed to know &lt;a href=\"Myriam%20Jahzia\"&gt;Myriam Jahzia&lt;/a&gt;, but these lines of dialogue were removed from the game when Jahzia was added. The &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; journal of the refers to Karyna having \"the gift of foresight\"; perhaps a holdover from her original conception."}
