{"id": "31998", "revid": "32712012", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31998", "title": "Kevin Griffith", "text": "Kevin Kanai Griffith was a member of &lt;a href=\"Team%203\"&gt;Team 3&lt;/a&gt;, and worked on environment design (e.g. randomization) for \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". This included &lt;a href=\"Icefall%20Caves\"&gt;Icefall Caves&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter Griffith succumbed to cancer, &lt;a href=\"Kanai%27s%20Cube\"&gt;Kanai's Cube&lt;/a&gt; was named after him. &lt;a href=\"King%20Kanai\"&gt;King Kanai&lt;/a&gt; was likewise designed after his 's appearance as a form of tribute, and &lt;a href=\"Udder%20Cowlamity\"&gt;Udder Cowlamity&lt;/a&gt; event is held in March (which is Kevin's birth month)."}
{"id": "23326", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23326", "title": "Kevin Martens", "text": "Kevin Martens is a lead designer for \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn addition to computer games, Martens is an accomplished chef, and likens the mixing of flavors in unexpected and enjoyable ways to the process of game design.\nBiography.\nMartens played \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\" when it came out. He called in sick for work in order to do so. When he encountered &lt;a href=\"The%20Butcher%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;The Butcher&lt;/a&gt;, his character died almost instantly.\nMartens's design experience stems back to at least 1999. Before joining &lt;a href=\"Blizzard%20Entertainment\"&gt;Blizzard Entertainment&lt;/a&gt;, he worked at BioWare, where he held leadership roles in the development of the \"Baldur's Gate\" series, \"Neverwinter Nights\", \"Jade Empire\", and \"Dragon Age: Origins\". He joined Blizzard in early 2009 as Lead Content Designer, becoming Lead Designer in early 2012. As lead designer on &lt;a href=\"Team%203\"&gt;Team 3&lt;/a&gt;, Martens is responsible for overseeing the creation and refinement of the game's levels, &lt;a href=\"classes\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt;, rules, story, and monster and treasure distribution, among other areas. He worked on the design of the &lt;a href=\"Crusader\"&gt;Crusader&lt;/a&gt;, inspiring its \"tank meets medieval warrior\" ethos."}
{"id": "6743", "revid": "865253", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6743", "title": "Key", "text": ""}
{"id": "29712", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29712", "title": "Key of Bones", "text": "Key of Bones was a miscellaneous &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20crafting%20material\"&gt;Legendary crafting material&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", and could be combined with the other three keys to create a &lt;a href=\"Infernal%20Machine\"&gt;portal device&lt;/a&gt; leading to one of the four realms of evil.\nIt can stacked up to a maximum of 5000, and is &lt;a href=\"account%20bound\"&gt;account bound&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis key could only be used to create an Infernal Machine for level 70. One such key was needed for each craft, regardless of which realm was chosen.\nAcquisition.\nKey of Bones dropped from &lt;a href=\"Odeg%20the%20Keywarden\"&gt;Odeg the Keywarden&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Fields%20of%20Misery\"&gt;Fields of Misery&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Torment\"&gt;Torment&lt;/a&gt; difficulty, only at level 70. If it dropped, it did for every member of the party.\nAs of patch 2.3, it no longer drops, existing Keys are transformed into Infernal Machines of corresponding type."}
{"id": "22548", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22548", "title": "Key of Destruction", "text": "The Key of Destruction is a quest item and may be used for:"}
{"id": "23876", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23876", "title": "Key of Destruction (Diablo III)", "text": "The Key of Destruction was a miscellaneous crafting material in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", it could be combined with other keys to create a &lt;a href=\"Infernal%20Machine\"&gt;machine of infernal power&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey have an &lt;a href=\"Item%20Level\"&gt;Item Level&lt;/a&gt; of 63 and require a character level of 1. They can be stacked up to a maximum of 100.\n\"\"The metal used to forge this warped and twisted key bears the mark of &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal\u2019s&lt;/a&gt; realm, but its contours suggest it is not complete.\"\"\nAcquisition.\nThe Key of Destruction used to drop from &lt;a href=\"Odeg%20the%20Keywarden\"&gt;Odeg the Keywarden&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Fields%20of%20Misery\"&gt;Fields of Misery&lt;/a&gt; in Act I\u00a0on\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Torment%20%28Difficulty%29\"&gt;Torment&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0I or higher difficulty at level 60-69.\u00a0It\u00a0is\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Bind%20on%20Account\"&gt;account bound&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs of patch 2.3, it no longer drops. Existing Keys automatically become Infernal Machines."}
{"id": "29714", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29714", "title": "Key of Evil", "text": "Key of Evil was a miscellaneous &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20crafting%20material\"&gt;Legendary crafting material&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", and could be combined with the other three keys to create a &lt;a href=\"Infernal%20Machine\"&gt;portal device&lt;/a&gt; leading to one of the four realms of evil.\nIt can stack up to a maximum of 5000, and is &lt;a href=\"account%20bound\"&gt;account bound&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis key could only be used to create an Infernal Machine for level 70. One such key was needed for each craft, regardless of which realm was chosen.\nAcquisition.\nKey of Evil dropped from &lt;a href=\"Nekarat%20the%20Keywarden\"&gt;Nekarat the Keywarden&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Gardens%20of%20Hope\"&gt;Gardens of Hope&lt;/a&gt; Second Tier at &lt;a href=\"Torment\"&gt;Torment&lt;/a&gt; difficulty, only at level 70. If it dropped, it did for every member of the party.\nAs of patch 2.3, it no longer drops, existing Keys are transformed into Infernal Machines of corresponding type."}
{"id": "29716", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29716", "title": "Key of Gluttony", "text": "Key of Gluttony was a miscellaneous &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20crafting%20material\"&gt;Legendary crafting material&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", and could be combined with the other three keys to create a &lt;a href=\"Infernal%20Machine\"&gt;portal device&lt;/a&gt; leading to one of the four realms of evil.\nIt can stacked up to a maximum of 5000, and is &lt;a href=\"account%20bound\"&gt;account bound&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis key could only be used to create an Infernal Machine for level 70. One such key was needed for each craft, regardless of which realm was chosen.\nAcquisition.\nKey of Gluttony dropped from &lt;a href=\"Xah%27Rith%20the%20Keywarden\"&gt;Xah'Rith the Keywarden&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Stonefort\"&gt;Stonefort&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Torment\"&gt;Torment&lt;/a&gt; difficulty, only at level 70. If it dropped, it did for every member of the party.\nAs of patch 2.3, it no longer drops, existing Keys are transformed into Infernal Machines of corresponding type."}
{"id": "22547", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22547", "title": "Key of Hate", "text": "The Key of Hate is a quest item and may be used for:"}
{"id": "23877", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23877", "title": "Key of Hate (Diablo III)", "text": "The Key of Hate was a miscellaneous crafting material in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", it could be combined with other keys to create a &lt;a href=\"Infernal%20Machine\"&gt;machine of infernal power&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey have an &lt;a href=\"Item%20Level\"&gt;Item Level&lt;/a&gt; of 63 and require a character level of 1. They can be stacked up to a maximum of 100.\n\"Simply touching this key fills one with a venomous hatred for all things. What power would be unleashed were this key to be combined with its brothers?\"\nAcquisition.\nThe Key of Hate dropped from &lt;a href=\"Sokahr%20the%20Keywarden\"&gt;Sokahr the Keywarden&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Dahlgur%20Oasis\"&gt;Dahlgur Oasis&lt;/a&gt; in Act II on &lt;a href=\"Torment%20%28Difficulty%29\"&gt;Torment&lt;/a&gt; I or higher difficulty at level 60-69.\u00a0It\u00a0is\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Bind%20on%20Account\"&gt;account bound&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs of patch 2.3, it no longer drops. Existing Keys automatically become Infernal Machines."}
{"id": "22549", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22549", "title": "Key of Terror", "text": "The Key of Terror is a quest item and may be used for:"}
{"id": "23878", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23878", "title": "Key of Terror (Diablo III)", "text": "The Key of Terror was a miscellaneous crafting material in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", it could be combined with other keys to create a &lt;a href=\"Infernal%20Machine\"&gt;machine of infernal power&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey have an &lt;a href=\"Item%20Level\"&gt;Item Level&lt;/a&gt; of 63 and require a character level of 1. They can be stacked up to a maximum of 100.\n\"\"Could this key really allow its bearer access to a &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Terror\"&gt;plane of unholy terror&lt;/a&gt;? Perhaps if its missing counterparts were found...\"\"\nAcquisition.\nThe Key of Terror dropped from &lt;a href=\"Xah%27Rith%20the%20Keywarden\"&gt;Xah'Rith the Keywarden&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Stonefort\"&gt;Stonefort&lt;/a&gt; in Act III\u00a0on\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Torment%20%28Difficulty%29\"&gt;Torment&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0I or higher difficulty at level 60-69.\u00a0It\u00a0is\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Bind%20on%20Account\"&gt;account bound&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs of patch 2.3, it no longer drops. Existing Keys automatically become Infernal Machines."}
