{"id": "29718", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29718", "title": "Key of War", "text": "Key of War was a miscellaneous &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20crafting%20material\"&gt;Legendary crafting material&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", and could be combined with the other three keys to create a &lt;a href=\"Infernal%20Machine\"&gt;portal device&lt;/a&gt; leading to one of the four realms of evil.\nIt can stacked up to a maximum of 5000, and is &lt;a href=\"account%20bound\"&gt;account bound&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis key could only be used to create an Infernal Machine for level 70. One such key was needed for each craft, regardless of which realm is chosen.\nAs of patch 2.3, it no longer drops, existing Keys are transformed into Infernal Machines of corresponding type.\nAcquisition.\nKey of War dropped from &lt;a href=\"Sokahr%20the%20Keywarden\"&gt;Sokahr the Keywarden&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Dahlgur%20Oasis\"&gt;Dahlgur Oasis&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Torment\"&gt;Torment&lt;/a&gt; difficulty, only at level 70. If it dropped, it did for every member of the party."}
{"id": "39568", "revid": "3467557", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39568", "title": "Keyed Dungeon", "text": "Keyed Dungeons are a gameplay feature of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". \nOverview.\nKeyed Dungeons introduce greater challenges as their tiers increase through dungeon affixes. The majority of dungeons are real places in &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;the world&lt;/a&gt;, and players will know some information about them including what types of &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s, events, and layouts to expect. With this information, as well as the specific dungeon affixes being displayed on the key, players will be able to strategize their approach before going into the dungeon."}
{"id": "3137", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3137", "title": "Keys", "text": "Keys are needed to open locked &lt;a href=\"Chests%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;chests&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\", unless you are an &lt;a href=\"Assassin\"&gt;Assassin&lt;/a&gt;. They can be purchased from NPCs in town in any act, or found outside of the towns. All keys are the same. They can be stacked up to 12 in an inventory square. Any size stack will simply be listed as \"Key\" on the ground, in the same way as &lt;a href=\"Arrows\"&gt;Arrows&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Bolts\"&gt;Bolts&lt;/a&gt;.\nMerchant Trade.\nCost 1 (Buy): 40 Gold\nCost 12 (Buy): 480 Gold\nCost 1 (Sell): 22 Gold\nCost 12 (Sell): 264 Gold"}
{"id": "29109", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29109", "title": "Keystone of Trials", "text": "Keystone of Trials\u00a0was a special Keystone for the &lt;a href=\"Nephalem%20Obelisk\"&gt;Nephalem Obelisk&lt;/a&gt;, used to open a portal to the &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Trials\"&gt;Realm of Trials&lt;/a&gt;. It was removed in patch 2.3.\nIt dropped from any &lt;a href=\"Rift%20Guardian\"&gt;Rift Guardian&lt;/a&gt; in a regular &lt;a href=\"Nephalem%20Rift\"&gt;Nephalem Rift&lt;/a&gt;, on level 70 and &lt;a href=\"Torment%20Difficulty\"&gt;Torment Difficulty&lt;/a&gt; only. The chance was very high, but was greatly reduced if the the player already had a Keystone of Trials in their &lt;a href=\"inventory\"&gt;inventory&lt;/a&gt; or shared &lt;a href=\"stash\"&gt;stash&lt;/a&gt;, or if the player had a &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Rift%20Keystone\"&gt;Greater Rift Keystone&lt;/a&gt;.\nEach stack of Keystones could hold up to 100 of them. They were &lt;a href=\"account%20bound\"&gt;account bound&lt;/a&gt;, and might not be sold or even dropped.\nIn patch 2.1, because of the way the Realm of Trials worked, should one venture in it with full inventory, it would be impossible to pick a Keystone (as one may not manage items while the Realm of Trials is opened). The only way to pick a Keystone in this case was to &lt;a href=\"salvage\"&gt;salvage&lt;/a&gt; something from the inventory, as salvaging works even while a Greater Rift portal is up. This issue has been fixed in patch 2.1.1."}
{"id": "25135", "revid": "174189", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=25135", "title": "Keywarden", "text": "Keywardens are four unique demons in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nTheir name comes from their original role: sometimes, upon death they would drop a key for the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Infernal%20Machine\"&gt;Infernal Machine&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0event. As of patch 2.3, they drop Infernal Machines of corresponding type instead.\nAt levels 61-70, all keywardens have a small chance to drop any level 70 device, which does not compete with their chance to drop their primary machine. This allows any keywarden to drop up to two devices upon death at levels 61-70. At level 60 or higher, they will be marked with a &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; icon on the map, and an arrow will point their location.\nAs of patch 2.4, their name also shows the material ultimately harvested from bosses in the realms for which they drop their machines."}
{"id": "26866", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26866", "title": "Khaaz", "text": "Khaaz, Deadly Serpent Fighter is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Deceiver\"&gt;Deceiver&lt;/a&gt; that can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Sewers%20of%20Caldeum\"&gt;Sewers of Caldeum&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nHe has Mortar, Desecrator and Fast affixes."}
{"id": "27663", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27663", "title": "Khahul the Serpent", "text": "Khahul the Serpent, Lord of Scales, is a unique found in the &lt;a href=\"Dahlgur%20Oasis\"&gt;Dahlgur Oasis&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe has Vortex and Plagued affixes."}
{"id": "2593", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2593", "title": "Khalim", "text": "Khalim was the one-time &lt;a href=\"Que-Hegan\"&gt;Que-Hegan&lt;/a&gt; of the High Council of the &lt;a href=\"Zakarum\"&gt;Zakarum&lt;/a&gt;. \nBiography.\nWhen the Priests of Zakarum were taken by the dark powers of &lt;a href=\"Mephisto\"&gt;Mephisto&lt;/a&gt;, the Lord of Hatred, Khalim alone remained on the side of &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt;. Enraged, Mephisto ordered the other council members to kill him. Khalim was slain and dismembered, and his remnants were scattered across &lt;a href=\"Nahantu\"&gt;Nahantu&lt;/a&gt;. He was succeeded as Que-Hegan by &lt;a href=\"Sankekur\"&gt;Sankekur&lt;/a&gt;, who would later become Mephisto's host. At the advice of &lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;Deckard Cain&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20II\"&gt;group of heroes&lt;/a&gt; gathered Khalim's &lt;a href=\"Khalim%27s%20Heart\"&gt;heart&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Khalim%27s%20Brain\"&gt;brain&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Khalim%27s%20Eye\"&gt;eye&lt;/a&gt;, in order to fashion a &lt;a href=\"Khalim%27s%20Flail\"&gt;flail&lt;/a&gt; that would shatter the &lt;a href=\"Compelling%20Orb\"&gt;Compelling Orb&lt;/a&gt;, allowing them to confront the Lord of Hatred.\nLegacy.\nIt is said that Khalim was incorruptible, and that his &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;spirit&lt;/a&gt; will never rest until Mephisto is vanquished for all time. He is the only Que-Hegan still venerated by the &lt;a href=\"Crusaders\"&gt;Crusaders&lt;/a&gt;.\nTowards the end of the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Enmity\"&gt;Great Enmity&lt;/a&gt; his flail was broken, though someone tried to repair it.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231336\"&gt;1336&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lorath%20Nahr\"&gt;Lorath Nahr&lt;/a&gt; speculated that Khalim's name was possibly invoked by those in battle, similar to other heroes of legend.\nIn-game.\nKhalim is the focus of the \"&lt;a href=\"Khalim%27s%20Will%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Khalim's Will&lt;/a&gt;\" quest in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\", where players must gather his body parts in order to forge &lt;a href=\"Khalim%27s%20Flail\"&gt;Khalim's Flail&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", he referenced in the &lt;a href=\"armor\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt;; &lt;a href=\"Shelter%20of%20Khalim\"&gt;Shelter of Khalim&lt;/a&gt;. A modification of &lt;a href=\"Conjuration%20of%20Light\"&gt;Conjuration of Light&lt;/a&gt; is named Khalim's Protection.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", he is referenced in the flavor text of &lt;a href=\"The%20Que-Hegan%27s%20Will\"&gt;The Que-Hegan's Will&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4388", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4388", "title": "Khalim's Brain", "text": "Khalim's Brain is one of the items needed to create the &lt;a href=\"Flail%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;flail&lt;/a&gt;, as part of the quest.\nIt can be found on level 3 of the &lt;a href=\"Flayer%20Dungeon\"&gt;Flayer Dungeon&lt;/a&gt; (not to be confused with the &lt;a href=\"Swampy%20Pit\"&gt;Swampy Pit&lt;/a&gt;, which is also in the &lt;a href=\"Flayer%20Jungle\"&gt;Flayer Jungle&lt;/a&gt;)."}
{"id": "4386", "revid": "1592487", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4386", "title": "Khalim's Eye", "text": "Khalim's Eye is one of the items that is needed to create &lt;a href=\"Khalim%27s%20Will%20%28Item%29\"&gt;Khalim's Will&lt;/a&gt;. It can be found at &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Cavern\"&gt;Spider Cavern&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"The%20Infernal%20Gate\"&gt;Act III&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4442", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4442", "title": "Khalim's Flail", "text": "Khalim's Flail is a &lt;a href=\"Quest%20Items\"&gt;quest item&lt;/a&gt; that is used for making &lt;a href=\"Khalim%27s%20Will%20%28Item%29\"&gt;Khalim's Will&lt;/a&gt;, and it is related to the &lt;a href=\"Khalim%27s%20Will%20%28quest%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; of the same name.\nThe flail can be used as a weapon, though even in &lt;a href=\"difficulty\"&gt;difficulty&lt;/a&gt;, it is an inferior weapon. Even a standard has higher base damage, with Khalim's Flail's bonus to &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Damage%29\"&gt;Lightning damage&lt;/a&gt; being its only advantage.\nStats.\n&lt;br&gt;\nOne-Hand Damage: 1 to 15&lt;br&gt;\nDurability: 30 of 30&lt;br&gt;\nRequired Dexterity: 35&lt;br&gt;\nRequired Strength: 41&lt;br&gt;\nMace Class - "}
{"id": "5790", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5790", "title": "Khalim's Heart", "text": "Khalim's Heart is one of the items needed to create &lt;a href=\"Khalim%27s%20Will%20%28Item%29\"&gt;Khalim's Will&lt;/a&gt; as part of the &lt;a href=\"Khalim%27s%20Will%20%28quest%29\"&gt;Khalim's Will&lt;/a&gt; quest. It can be found on level 2 of the &lt;a href=\"Kurast%20Sewers\"&gt;Kurast Sewers&lt;/a&gt;."}
